title: baked spaghetti
directions: Simmer for 3 hours.
(Watch closely and stir often; wants to stick.)
Cook spaghetti and put in a pan.
Pour sauce over spaghetti; cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Put in oven and brown the cheese.

title: tangy broiled potato slices
directions: Preheat broiler (if manufacturer directs).
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Toss potatoes with 2 tablespoons Italian dressing.
Place potato slices on rack in broiling pan.
Place pan in broiler at closest position to heat.
Broil potatoes 15 minutes or until tender, turning once and brushing with the remaining dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: italian chicken
directions: Deskin and debone chicken breasts and cut into pieces.
Mix eggs with water and spices.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture and then into bread crumbs to coat.
Fry chicken pieces until golden (do not over fry).

title: candied yams
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine sugar, 3/4 stick margarine, water and cinnamon; bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
When potatoes are tender, top with mixture of brown sugar, 1/4 cup melted butter, flour and chopped nuts mixed well. Return to oven and bake about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In small bowl, combine crumbs and parsley.
In separate bowl, combine Ranch dressing and water.
Dip chicken in mixture, then into crumb mix, coating well.
Spray nonstick on baking pan, arrange chicken and bake 8 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, salt, pepper and mustard, and cook to a boil.
Add eggs and stir constantly until thick.
Beat in salad dressing and toss in celery and onions.
Pour over cooked potatoes and toss gently.
Add 2 cooked eggs (optional).

title: lemon honey yummy
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in honey, lemon juice and rind; chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Beat gelatin with hand beater until fluffy, then fold in whipped topping.
Spread 1/2 the crumbs in bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Spoon in gelatin mixture and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Cut into squares.
Garnish with twisted lemon slices, if desired. Makes about 4 1/2 cups or 8 servings.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 3 hours on low.
Serve with Fritos.
Enjoy!

title: sour cream lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook noodles as per directions.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan noodles, hamburger, sauce and cheeses, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add coconut extract, milk, flour and coconut. Beat all together and bake in well-greased tube pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet condensed milk
directions: Dissolve dry milk in water.
Stir in sugar.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over orange sherbet. Drink.

title: bair's salad
directions: Place on individual salad plates and top with Bair's Salad dressing and slivered almonds.

title: mini cheese blintzes
directions: Blend cream cheese, yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Remove crusts from bread.
Roll each slice thin with a rolling pin.
Spread about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture onto each slice of bread; roll up like a jellyroll.
Roll in melted butter and then cinnamon and sugar.
Cut roll in half.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 95.
Can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen until ready to bake.

title: cheddar pecan spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Serve with assorted vegetables and crackers.
This spread can be refrigerated up to 3 weeks.

title: mint fizz
directions: Put chopped mint in pitcher with sugar.
Pour boiling water over and leave to cool.
Then add freshly squeezed juices.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours in the refrigerator.
Strain.
Add ginger ale or soda and ice cubes.
Pour in glasses and garnish with mint sprigs and serve.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Note:
Can add any candied fruit preferred.

title: breast of chicken en papillote
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place breasts in small pot and add chicken broth to barely cover.
Bring to boil and reduce heat; cover and simmer gently until tender (25 to 45 minutes).
Remove from broth and cool.
Remove skin and bones from breasts carefully.
Cut 6 pieces aluminum foil large enough to make an envelope for each breast half and spread with 1/2 of butter.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients, then make hole in center.
Mix remaining ingredients and put in hole.
Mix all ingredients well, then put in 4 greased and floured coffee cans or whatever you want to bake it in.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add all ingredients together, adding cornbread mix last.
Bake in greased muffin tins for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
This makes 12 muffins plus an 8-inch round pan full.

title: calumet sugar cookies
directions: Cream fat and sugar; beat in whipped eggs. Add baking powder and 1 cup flour, then water and spices. Add remaining flour gradually, working in more flour until dough is stiff enough to roll. Sprinkle flour over pastry board. Make a ball of dough and lay it on the board. Rub rolling pin with flour and roll out dough into 2 sheets, 1/4-inch thick. Cut in round cakes. Sift granulated sugar over each and bake quickly at 400° to 450°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk until well blended.
Gradually beat in flour until smooth.
Pour into funnel with 1/2-inch opening.
Pour into hot oil; fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Rinse lamb; pat dry with a paper towel.
Rub seasoned salt all over roast.
Slice cloves of garlic and slip under skin.
Wrap in heavy aluminum foil.
Let set a few hours on a rack in a roasting pan.
Cook fat side up at 325° until done (about 2 1/2 hours).
Let set 20 minutes before slicing.
Cut across grain.
Reserve stock for gravy.

title: snowy white chocolate crescents
directions: In small bowl, combine flour and cocoa.
Mix well with wire whisk.
In a medium bowl, cream butter and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and cocoa mix.
Blend on low speed until fluffy. The dough will dry and crumble.
Shape a level tablespoon of dough into a 3 1/2-inch log to form a crescent shape.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° (1-inch apart).
Bake 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: orzo with garlic
directions: Bring water to boil and add salt.
Add orzo and cook, stirring about 10 mins. or till tender.
Reserve 1/4 c. of cooking liquid.
Drain orzo.
Meanwhile, heat oil and butter
in saucepan. Add garlic and cook, do not brown.
Add orzo, reserved liquid and rest of ingredients.
Toss well and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Mix with enough water to make soft meat balls.
Fry or bake them and then simmer a half hour in gravy.

title: fran's slush(no sugar)
directions: Boil 2 cups water with 2 green tea bags.
Let cool.
In very large container place 7 cups water, orange juice, lemonade, tea and liquor.
mix well.
Put mixture into smaller containers and place in freezer.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with Karo syrup.
Gradually add evaporated milk and egg stirring to blend.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 375° until top is brown and just begins to crack (about 40 minutes).
Cool at least 3 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, celery, oranges and nuts.
Add sugar and 2 boxes of cherry jello.
Mix all together and put in bowl until set.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Select fresh blossoms, being careful that all the stems have been removed.
Pour boiling water over flowers and let stand for 3 days.
Strain; add remaining ingredients and let stand 3 weeks until fermented.
Strain bottle and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: collard greens
directions: Use as much water as it takes to cook collards in; use as little water as possible.
Gather collards.
Pick and wash them; cut them up.
Have the other ingredients boiling.
Put them in pot and cook for about 2 hours or until done at low heat.

title: ding how casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish, in order listed, in layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the crumbs with butter and pat into the bottom of a spring-form pan.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and egg yolks until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add flour; fold into first mixture and pour over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: potato balls(kotleciki z kartofli)
directions: Peel each potato; cover with water and add 2 ounces salt. Cook until tender.
Drain well and place in mixing machine; add seasonings, butter and onion powder and mix well.
(Instant mashed potatoes can be added if consistency is too loose.)
When potato mixture is cooled, shape into small balls.
Dip into beaten egg yolks and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until brown.
Best to fry them just before serving.
Makes approximately 75.

title: mochiko chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients and soak chicken overnight.
Fry in vegetable oil and serve.

title: mom's creamy cheesecake
directions: Cream softened cream cheese, adding eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and beat at medium speed for 10 minutes. Butter and flour 9-inch spring-form pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave cheesecake in oven for 1 hour, without opening door.
Turns out great every time.
Freezes well.

title: date delight
directions: Combine water, salt and dates.
Cook until thick and mushy. Add marshmallows and stir.
They will melt.
Crush Oreos in a bag, filling and all.
Add about 1/2 of crushed Oreos in bottom of square glass dish.
Add date mix in globs, being careful not to scoot Oreos.
Smooth carefully.
Top all with whipped cream.
Then add the rest of the Oreos on top.
Refrigerate at least overnight.

title: roast beef sandwiches
directions: Place roast in roasting pan and bake, uncovered, at 275° for 1 hour.
Dissolve bouillon and soup mix in water.
Pour over the roast.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Remove meat and slice thinly.
Return to pan juices and heat through.
Serve on buns or rolls.
Yields about 24 to 30 servings.

title: coca-cola salad(good)
directions: Let mixture of the first 3 ingredients cool, then add the Coke.
When mixture starts to thicken, add the pecans, cherries and pineapple.
Refrigerate and allow to set.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Stir in peanuts and cook until peanuts and syrup are light brown.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: cherry "o" cheese pie
directions: Mix and pour first 4 ingredients in pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix salt and vanilla with buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.
Mix soda and vinegar. Add last, folding in (don't beat).
Bake in 2 layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice water pickles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large container and layer with salt and ice cubes.
Let stand 3 hours.
Mix spices, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: sunday cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet.
Drain and save grease.
Crumble bacon.

title: chocolate covered teacher
directions: First put the dry ingredients in a bowl.
Mix for fifteen minutes. Put the egg in a separate bowl and beat for five minutes. Now add all remaining ingredients to first bowl and mix for twenty minutes.
Cook in a 350° oven for 56 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish with potatoes.
Heat soup and add margarine and cream cheese until melted.
Gradually add milk.
Pour over potatoes and cover dish with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and add 1 heaping cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with fruit.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, rice, onion, bell pepper, salt, celery salt and garlic.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
In deep skillet, heat tomato juice, cloves, spices, sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Drop meatballs in sauce and simmer for 1 hour.

title: coconut mounds balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into balls.
Chill for about 1 hour then dip in chocolate coating.

title: apple pie drink
directions: Mix all ingredients except alcohol and bring to boil. Simmer 30 minutes. Remove from heat and cool completely. Add alcohol. Enjoy!!

title: weight watchers milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend on high until smooth.
You may substitute for strawberries 1/2 frozen banana, frozen pitted cherries, frozen peaches, frozen apples or frozen pineapple.
Contains approximately 150 calories with 9 grams fat or freeze milk, omit fruit and add imitation flavoring (contains 80 calories with 0 grams fat).
You won't miss ice cream anymore.

title: sunday fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large serving bowl.
Mix well. Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In a large bowl, combine marshmallows and peanuts.
Set aside. Line sides and bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with waxed paper. Rub paper lightly with a bit of butter or margarine.
In a saucepan, combine chocolate pieces, condensed milk and butter or margarine.
Heat over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat and combine with marshmallows and peanuts.
Quickly spread into the lined pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan and peel off waxed paper.
Cut into 1-inch squares with a wet knife.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Makes about 8 dozen.
Quick and very good.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops on both sides in a skillet over medium heat; pour off excess fat.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Drain the peaches, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Mix reserved peach syrup, corn syrup, lemon juice, cinnamon, ginger and cloves; pour over chops.
Cover pan; cook over low heat for 45 minutes, or until pork is done.
Add the peach halves; heat through.
Remove chops and peach halves to a serving platter and keep warm.
Mix the flour and water; stir into the liquid in skillet.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, then spoon over chops.
Makes 6 servings.

title: flying farmer salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight (or several hours) in refrigerator.
May add more chicken.

title: hopping john
directions: Cook peas according to directions.
Cook sausage and onions in skillet and add black-eyed peas and uncooked rice onto mixture. Continue to cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with cornbread. Really good!
Minute rice can be used.
As water as needed and also seasoning.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello	in 1/2 cup of hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together with mixer. Bake in four greased and floured one pound coffee cans at 350° for 1 hour.
Fill cans one-half full.

title: jiffy fruit cocktail cobbler
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan while preheating the oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine the flour, sugar and baking powder with a spoon.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Stir into the melted margarine that is in the pan.
Spoon the fruit evenly over the batter.
Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin and water in heated soup.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly.
Add cream cheese.
Mix until cream cheese is thoroughly blended (no lumps).
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into loaf pan or mold and chill (preferably overnight).
When mixture is set, remove from mold and place on bed of lettuce.
May be served as salad, dip or spread.

title: pete's ham what am
directions: Remove tough skin from ham and score top.
Place in flat pan in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over ham.
The last hour baste frequently.
Last 1/2 hour pour 1/2 to 1 can ginger ale over ham and continue basting.
Let cool before carving.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Cook frozen cauliflower according to package directions. Drain cauliflower and place in greased 1-quart casserole.
Pour soup (no water) over cauliflower.
Mix crumbs with margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in oblong 2-quart baking dish in oven while mixing other ingredients (except fruit).
In mixing bowl, stir together first four ingredients.
Pour batter on melted oleo (do not stir). Add fruit evenly on top of unstirred batter in baking dish.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: almond stuffed dates with bacon
directions: Stuff each date with an almond.
Cut bacon strips into thirds and wrap a piece around each date.
Secure with a round wooden toothpick.
Put the dates on a foil lined baking sheet and bake in a preheated oven at 400° until bacon is crisp, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain on a rack or paper towels.

title: pecan chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breast halves to 1/4-inch thickness.
In saucepan, melt 6 tablespoons butter.
Whisk in half of mustard until blended; put in shallow bowl.
Put pecans in another shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in butter mixture, then in pecans.
In a large frying pan, heat remaining butter in oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 3 minutes on each side.
Put in a baking dish and keep warm in a 200° oven until sauce is done.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons of fat from frying pan and then heat on low.
Add sour cream, remaining mustard, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Cook until heated through (do not boil).
Serve over chicken.
Also great over white rice!

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat margarine and oil in large pan.
Add onions and garlic and fry very gently for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in the flour and cook another 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in the stock gradually, then add wine.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and cover. Simmer gently for 20 to 25 minutes or until the onions are soft.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or cook in crock-pot for 5 hours.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Chill 1 hour before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients together, pour over broccoli; sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs on top. Slice pats of butter or margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cheddar breakfast muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottoms only of 15 muffin cups or line.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir by hand 60 strokes. Divide batter among 15 cups. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: sweet-sour chops and cabbage
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Brown slowly in T-Fal pan.
Add onion, vinegar and tomato juice. Cover and cook over low heat until chops are tender, about 50 minutes. Add cabbage. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover. Cook 10 minutes. Remove chops.
Toss cabbage in sauce and serve, placing chops on top of cabbage.

title: apple salad(every year i make this for my thanksgiving dinner.)
directions: Core apples and cut, but don't peel.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add salad dressing and mix some more. Ready to eat!
Serves 12 to 15.

title: bacon-cauliflower salad
directions: The night before serving, layer lettuce, onion, bacon and cauliflower into a bowl with a tight fitting cover.
Sprinkle sugar, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper over top. Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Mix well before serving.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Let cranberries and sugar set overnight.
Mix all together and let chill.

title: buttery pecans(appetizer in microwave)
directions: Place nuts in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Dot with butter.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir until butter coats the nuts evenly.

title: festive stuffed pea pods
directions: In a saucepan bring 2 cups water to a full boil; add pea pods, cook 1 minute.
Drain well; put into ice water, drain well, cut off stems.
Cut a seam on the side of pea pods forming a pocket, set aside.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover,
bring
to
a boil and simmer over medium heat for 7 minutes, or heat in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: beet jelly
directions: Mix together beet juice, Sure-Jell and lemon juice.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add sugar and boil 6 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix 1 stick of butter and oatmeal.
Add 1 1/4 c. boiling water and let stand 20 minutes.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla, cinnamon, pecans and 1 c. flour, 1 c. brown sugar, 1 c. white sugar, salt, baking soda and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. While cake is baking have topping ready.

title: rice salad
directions: Drain oil from artichokes and add to salad dressing.
Mix all together; salt and pepper lightly.
May add a pinch of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon curry powder, if desired.
Ham, chicken or shrimp is added at the last.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine ingredients; toss to mix well.
Refrigerate until served.
Serve on crisp dry greens.
Save a few nutmeats to sprinkle on top of the salad.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Heat greased 7-inch nonstick pan on stove top until hot.
Pour batter into pan.
If too thick, add 2 to 3 tablespoons water. Cover pan.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes over low heat until top of corn bread is firm.
Flip corn bread over and cook 5 to 10 minutes uncovered.
Cool on rack.
Serve with honey and/or butter.

title: hamburger gooiloush
directions: Make beef patties small, then dump tomatoes, onions and new potatoes together.
Cook until potatoes are done and serve.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons.

title: pasta with peas, prosciutto and parmesan
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Add shallots and saute over low heat 5 minutes.
Stir in cream, basil and Prosciutto.
Cook until thickened to a good coating consistency (about 15 minutes).

title: german meat loaf
directions: Work all together to form a ball; flatten slightly.
Brown in a Dutch oven on both sides.
Put water halfway up and simmer 20 minutes on both sides.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In skillet, combine gelatin, cinnamon, water and salt.
Add margarine.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add sweet potatoes; cover and cook 15 minutes or until sweet potatoes are glazed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in clean jar.
Also makes a nice gift. To serve, add 2 to 3 teaspoons to hot water.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend oil and sugars until mixed well.
Add vanilla; beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. In another bowl, stir together flour, milk powder, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture until well blended.
By hand, stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured (lightly) ring microwave pan.
Microwave on Roast 4 minutes or until done.
Bake in convection oven 20 minutes at 325°.
Bake in regular oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If baking in regular oven be sure to use proper pan.
Try this recipe as cupcakes, muffins or quick bread.
Frost with powdered sugar or cream cheese frosting or just plain.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese together.
Fold in strawberries, pineapple, marshmallows, bananas, Cool Whip and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Makes 6 quarts or 2 gallons.
Serve hot.

title: carolyn's crumb crust apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter baking dish or pie plate.
Put in sliced apples and pour water over them.
Sprinkle on cinnamon. Work together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread over apples mixture and bake slowly, uncovered, 1 hour or until apples are tender.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Let drain.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Boil rice.
Combine chicken, rice, cream of mushroom and 1/2 can of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in oven on 300° about 20 minutes.
Top with cheese just before removing from oven.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: lemon filling
directions: Beat all together and boil until thick in a double boiler. Spread between layers of cake.
Put grated rind in batter.
Makes filling for 3 layers.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Fill cupcake papers 1/2 full; set aside.
In separate bowl, mix the cream cheese, sugar, egg, salt and chocolate chips.
Beat this mixture and put 1 teaspoon on top of uncooked cake batter.
Bake at 350° until done.
Top with cream cheese icing, if desired.

title: cheese and bacon quiche
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a mixing bowl.
Rub in the butter until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs.
Stir in enough water to bind together and form into a dough.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Roll out the pastry and use to line a greased 10-inch cake pan or flan ring placed on a baking sheet.

title: vegetable hollandaise sauce
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add to egg yolks gradually, stirring.
Return to double boiler and stir constantly over boiling water until thick.
Remove sauce from hot water and add lemon juice and salt, stirring.
Cover and again place over hot water.
Add onion and celery.
Remove from fire and leave over hot water until time to serve.
Sauce may be made 30 to 45 minutes before time to serve.
Serve over any vegetable desired.

title: rods bar-b-q ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with Grill Mates Montreal Steak Seasoning. Mix all of the ingredients above together. Place ribs in and let sit for 2 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and pour into 3 (8-inch) round cake pans; bake.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple nut dip
directions: Beat the sour cream, cream cheese and cinnamon in a medium bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients; chill. Serve with fruit dippers, pound cake or angel food cubes, if desired.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Preparation time:
15 minutes plus refrigerating.

title: cream cheese pie(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Add all ingredients in blender, beginning with milk and eggs. Cut cream cheese into chunks.
Blend on high speed for about 1 minute or until mixture is thick and custard-like.
Pour into pie shell.
Place pie shell on cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
If center of pie is runny, bake about 5 minutes longer.
Remove pie and let cool.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine and mix well. Pour over first 4 ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Keeps well. (Yield: 6 to 8 servings.)

title: buttermilk griddle cakes
directions: Sift the flour with salt, baking soda, baking powder, corn meal and sugar.
Beat eggs and add buttermilk and shortening.
Add sifted ingredients and beat until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls on hot griddle.
When full of bubbles, turn to brown on other side.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Spray crock-pot with nonstick spray.
Melt chocolate chips. Mix with the next 7 ingredients.
Pour into crock-pot.
Heat water and dissolve the sugar.
Pour over top of the mixture.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pasta with spinach, beans and cheese(low fat vegetarian dish)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, lightly grease a large (12 inch) nonstick skillet.
Heat over medium-high heat; when hot, add tomatoes and garlic.
Cook and stir about 2 minutes, or until tomatoes are slightly soft. Stir in beans, broth and spinach.
Cook until spinach just wilts, stirring constantly.
Drain pasta well and add to skillet.
Stir in cheeses, and season with freshly ground pepper.
Toss lightly and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.
350 calories, 4 g. fat, 465 mg. calcium per serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt the Velveeta in crock-pot on low.
Fry ground beef.
Add the onion mix.
Stir in taco sauces.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread filling in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter; sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: play clay
directions: Need to take deviled eggs to a picnic or luncheon?
Instead of slicing eggs lengthwise, slice them in half and put back into the egg carton to stuff.
The egg cartons easily fit into ice chest, the eggs do not get messy and the carton serves as the serving plate when you get to your destination.

title: perfect peach cake
directions: Follow directions on package to prepare cake mix. Pour into a lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Place in 13 x 9-inch pan in order.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice onion thin.
Salt cucumbers as you slice.
Add sugar and 1 cup vinegar.
Leave salted cukes in container for 2 hours.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Heat sugar and vinegar; cool.
Pour over cukes.
Put into freezer cups and place into freezer.

title: glazed chicken and vegetables
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry and place breast side up on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Brush with oil.
Roast, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 1/2 hour.
After the first 1/2 hour, place vegetables (potatoes and carrots) around the chicken.
Then cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: no-roll pie crust
directions: Measure flour, salt and sugar into 9-inch pie pan.
Mix with fork.
Combine oil and milk; pour onto flour mixture.
Mix with fork.
Press by hand into bottom and sides of pan.
Flute the rim.
Prick the crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix water and soda.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add flour, sugar, egg, vanilla, dates, water, brown sugar and butter.
Boil all ingredients 10 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen grapes
directions: Wash and clean the grapes.
Take grapes off stem and put in Ziploc bag.
Put in freezer.
Enjoy as a snack.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Broil meat or barbecue.
Great marinade for chicken, too!

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Heat oven

Drain fat from pan. In same pan, cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.	Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with condensed milk. Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts. Spread evenly onto aluminum foil lined 8 or 9-inch pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm. Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares. Store loosely at room temperature.

title: lye soap
directions: Mix lye in water.
Be sure to use granite container large enough to leave soap in to harden.
Add melted grease.
Stir carefully.
Let harden.
When it is hard, cut it out in cubes. Grate it up and use as washing powder.
You'll be surprised how white and clean your clothes are.

title: pecan chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: make-ahead lettuce salad
directions: In a six quart bowl, layer half of the lettuce, onion, celery, green pepper, water chestnuts and peas.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar; spread half over the salad.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon if desired. Cover and refrigerate for 12-24 hours. Yields 14-16 servings.

title: smoked salmon and gruyere cheesecake with mini bagels(16 to 20 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9-inch cheesecake pan with butter.
Line bottom with a buttered wax paper circle and dust the bottom and sides of pan with 3 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese. Set aside.
Saute the onion in the oil over medium heat until soft, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add garlic, dill and salmon.
Season with salt, pepper and cayenne and set aside.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: 1st Layer:
Bread (cut off crust); cut into bite size pieces. Place in bottom of a greased casserole dish.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in a saucepan.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Cook slowly at low heat until thickened; about 15 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Heat oil in a skillet. Brown onion and ground beef.
Stir in cheese, seasonings and rice. Set aside.

title: mexican party dip
directions: Brown hamburger; add taco seasoning packet.
In another bowl, mix together sour cream and cheeses.
Reserve some of shredded cheese for topping.
Place cheese mixture in bottom of a large ovenproof casserole dish.
Follow with hamburger mixture.
Next, add salsa and top with remaining shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together in any order in bowl.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°; do not overbake.
When sides first begin to pull away, it's done.

title: three-fruit sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container. Switch blender on and off until mixture is well blended. Pile into freezer tray; freeze until firm. Serve in sherbet glasses and top with cherry.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Work all together and press in bottom of a long cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together. Crumble bacon on top.
Serve with buttermilk dressing.

title: simple mexican style chicken
directions: Layer chicken in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with picante sauce and bake at 400° about 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese before serving.

title: cheddar crabmeat
directions: Blend all ingredients together; spread on muffins.
Cut muffins in quarters.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Broil to crisp the tops.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Optional ingredients:
Chopped apples, walnuts, raisins, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon or top with brown sugar raisins.

title: chicketti
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool.
Remove meat from bones.
Cut in good sized pieces.
Combine chicken broth, consomme, mushrooms and mushroom soup and heat to boiling.
Saute onions, pepper and celery.
Sprinkle with paprika; add pimento.
Add spaghetti.
Cook until tender.
Fold in olives and 1 cup cheese.
Serve on platter. Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: whiskey sour
directions: Boil 2 cups of the water with 4 tea bags.
Simmer and turn off. Mix in bowl hot tea mix, sugar, orange juice, lemonade, whiskey and 5 cups cold water.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Mix slush, 1/2 and 1/2 with 7-Up.

title: 5 minute cheesecake
directions: Fold Cool Whip into lemonade and condensed milk. Pour into crust. Freeze. Thaw for 30 minutes (or less) prior to serving. Store unused pie in freezer.

title: montana pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick as for pizza dough.
Spread in large cake pan or pizza pan.
Bake at 325° until done.
Put pizza sauce, hamburger, eggs and onions on.
Mushrooms and peppers may be added, if desired.
Spread undiluted soup on top.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb oat crumble
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients, then add margarine and rub with fingers until no lumps.
Press half of mixture into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Evenly put rhubarb over crumbs.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat together lemon cake mix and eggs until smooth.
Fold in the lemon pie filling.
Bake according to the box directions.

title: double-decker finger jello
directions: In large bowl, combine Knox with flavored Jell-O.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Stir in whipping cream.
Pour into shallow baking pan.
Chill until firm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Pour rice evenly in casserole.
Top with onion soup.
Pour water over rice and soup.
Brown chops (do not cook), place on top of casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut top off of potatoes.
Take potato out and mix with chives, sour cream, grated cheese, salt, pepper, onion and enough milk to have desired consistency.
Put potatoes back in potato peel.
Sprinkle with grated cheese on top and bake until hot.

title: best blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all together and stir well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Butter 2-quart casserole.
Microwave butter and cheese until melted.
Mix until smooth.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix until smooth. Put apples and juice in dish.
Put cheese mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Have buttermilk at room temperature.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in the shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk, all at once.
Stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out and knead 1/2 minute.
Roll 3/8-inch thick.
Brush with melted fat or salad oil.
Cut out with a biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in hot oven at 450°.
Keep dough moist.
Makes 2 dozen small biscuits.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening (if using shortening).
Combine oil with buttermilk (if using oil).
Mix in buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Roll out on floured board 1 inch thick; cut.
Place in pan; let set 15 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken-n-dressing
directions: Melt butter in pan, then stir in stuffing.
Stir rest of ingredients together in bowl.
Spread 1/2 stuffing into bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch), then dump in the other mixture.
Spread rest of stuffing over top.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cranberry sauce, mashed potatoes and broccoli.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Microwave the celery and onion for a couple of minutes. Combine all ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle saved chips over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: rice and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix rice, sauteed celery, fish, eggs and lemon juice.
Fold in mayonnaise and soup and season to taste.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Top with onion rings or mix in as they tend to get too brown.
Can add them 5 minutes before finished.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix in glass jar.
Shake very thoroughly.
This can be doubled and stored in refrigerator.
Shake thoroughly before each use.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased pan or Pyrex for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, tomato, broccoli and celery. Drain off fat.
Pour in
water and cook, covered, for 2 minutes. In another pot, prepare macaroni and cheese.
When it's finished, add it to the meat mixture. Stir together and serve.

title: mean salad
directions: Mix all dressing ingredients together and refrigerate for eight hours.

title: pork chops with cheese topping
directions: Brown chops in skillet with oil.
Combine next 6 ingredients in bowl.
Remove chops and place on broiler pan; top with cheese mixture and broil for several minutes until lightly browned.
Heat wine and water in pan drippings.
Pour over chops; serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl; beat on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake 55 to 65 minutes until toothpick stuck in center of bread comes out clean.
Cool.

title: jello pudding jigglers or creamy jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely; cool to room temperature, about 30 minutes.

title: dad's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Set aside.
Break spaghetti noodles into bite size pieces. Cook according to directions; drain and rinse.
Combine ground beef and cooked spaghetti.
Add tomato juice.
Heat until warm.

title: caramel french toast
directions: In a medium saucepan combine brown sugar, 3/4 cup butter and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 5 min. or until bubbly.
Pour syrup evenly into lightly greased 9 x 13 in. baking dish.
Place bread slices over syrup.
Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Stir well and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over soaked bread. Drizzle 1/4
melted butter over top.
Bake uncovered 45-50 min. or until golden and bubbly.
Yields 10 servings.

title: crispy herb chicken
directions: Preheat gas oven to 400°.
Put butter in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan and place in oven until melted.
Meanwhile, combine crushed stuffing and salt in a plastic or brown paper bag.
Dip chicken pieces into egg that has been beaten with water, then shake chicken, a few pieces at a time, in the bag until well coated.
Place chicken, skin side down, in melted butter.
Do not layer in pan.
Bake uncovered in 400° oven 30 minutes.
Turn and continue baking for 30 minutes or until tender.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: harriet nelson's cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, the 2/3 cup sugar and almond extract together very thoroughly or until smooth and thick and lemon colored.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.
While cheese cake is cooling, beat sour cream, the 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla together thoroughly.
Pour sour cream mixture over top of cheese cake. Return to 350° oven and bake 10 minutes more.
Cool before serving. Sprinkle slivered Brazil nuts on top before serving.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) cake.

title: mike's favorite biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Roll out and cut in strips; any size of rectangles will do. Dip each piece into the melted butter. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. Wonderful!

title: strawberry squish
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with remainder of strawberries.

title: best brownies(pam smith's favorite)
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Add eggs; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie pulls away from pan. Cool; frost with Creamy Brownie Frosting.
Cut into squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread peaches in syrup in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sprinkle dry cake mix in even layer over top of peaches.
Cut butter in thin slices.
Place over cake mix.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 35 minutes.
(May use apple pie filling in place of peaches.)
Serves 12.

title: supper salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients and put in mold or Pyrex container.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corned beef hash
directions: In a wooden bowl, put 3 cups of cold boiled potatoes and 4 cups of cold corned beef from which gristle and fat have been removed. Chop until meat and potatoes are fine.
Place frying pan on the stove.
Melt a piece of real butter about the size of 2 eggs in frying pan.
Add a cup of boiling water to butter, then chopped potatoes and corned beef.
Stir until hot.
Turn heat as low as possible.
Tamp down hash in pan; let set on low heat to form a brown crust on the lower side of the hash.
With a broad-bladed knife, fold hash like an omelet and serve.

title: creamy cherry chocolate frosting
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over boiling water.
In mixing bowl, combine confectioners sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate mixture, blending well.
Chill 10 minutes.
Beat until of spreading consistency.
Stir in cherries.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place ingredients in blender; cover and blend 1 minute.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes its own crust.

title: all bean salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Rinse kidney beans well.
Cut onions small, also pepper.
Fry diced bacon crisp and drain well. Do not use grease!
Mix all well.
Top with crisp bacon bits.

title: beef and tortellini soup
directions: Cook ground beef and place in crock-pot. Add tomatoes, onion soup, green beans, basil, kidney beans, water and zucchini. Turn crock-pot on low setting. Cook for 4 or 5 hours. About 10 or 15 minutes before serving, add tortellini to soup. Continue cooking in crock-pot. Serve with grated cheese on top.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the following: chicken breast halves, Swiss cheese slices and soup (undiluted).
Mix stuffing mix with melted butter and pour on top.
Cook at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes, covered with foil.
Enjoy!

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches with juice into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry jello over peaches.
Cut margarine into small pieces and dot the top of cake mix.
Sprinkel water (with a teaspoon) over entire surface carefully.
Do not pour.
Do not stir.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mid morning souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cube.
Place bread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Combine milk, eggs, grated cheese and seasoning in blender.
Pour over bread, making sure it is all moistened.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into a ball; garnish with chopped nuts, parsley, etc.
Serve with crackers.

title: party chicken
directions: Separate beef and place a few slices under each chicken breast which has been wrapped in bacon.
Place in a greased pan.
Mix undiluted soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken breasts, and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered. Bake an additional 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: hominy pie
directions: Brown meat; add flour, tomatoes and seasonings.
Brown hominy and onion in hot fat.
Add to meat mixture.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares.
In large skillet, brown on all sides in hot shortening.
Remove from skillet.
Add gravy mix and water.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except noodles).
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Boil noodles as directed.
Serve mixture over hot noodles.

title: chocolate peanut butter ribbon fudge
directions: Mix together peanut butter, powdered sugar and melted butter; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine chocolate pieces, butter slices, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Heat granulated sugar and evaporated milk in a saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over chocolate mixture in bowl and stir until thoroughly blended.
Turn half of chocolate mixture into well buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Carefully spoon reserved peanut butter mixture over fudge layer, spreading evenly.
Turn remaining fudge over peanut butter mixture and carefully spread evenly. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares and serve or give in individual paper candy cups.
Makes 5 dozen pieces of fudge.

title: ham-ripe olive tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Drain ripe olives and chop coarsely.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well.
Return to pan.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and mix well.
Spoon buttered noodles around edge of casserole.

title: chicken kiev
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter.
On piece of wax paper, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then roll in crumbs to coat.
Place, skin side up, in ungreased (I remove skin) baking dish (9-inch square).
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and tender.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Combine margarine and brown sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Brownies will rise, then fall.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: ella's orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter with electric mixer until light in color.
Add all remaining ingredients, blend on low speed, scraping down sides of bowl several times.
The dough is sticky in appearance.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased sheet.
Bake in preheated oven for approximately 10 minutes.
Cookies will have a puffed surface and the edges will be lightly browned when done. Cool slightly on cookie sheet, then remove.
Ice while warm for a glazed look or cool for a regular iced look.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package.
Combine milk and ground beef.
Divide into 5 patties on waxed paper.
Pat each to 6 inches wide.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each and draw meat over stuffing.
Seal.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fat-free chocolate cupcakes
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine Jell-O, dry milk, cocoa, sugar and flour. Set aside. With electric mixer, beat alternately into the egg mixture a cup at a time with the vanilla, applesauce and baking soda which have been mixed together. Beat 2 minutes after the last addition. Bake at 350° about 18 to 20 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes, then remove.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter. Line 9-inch pie tin with pastry.
Pour pecans into crust and add mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pecans will rise to top to form a crust.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together with a mixer. Place in 8 x 8 dish. Top with salsa. Sprinkle cheese and green onions on top of salsa. Refrigerate.

title: kristiana kringler(bread)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients for pie crust.
Divide in half.
On ungreased cookie sheet, press into two 3-inch strips the length of the sheet (using the heel of your hand).

title: rice and chicken bake
directions: Put butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt in oven.
Remove pan and add chopped onions and savory leaves.
Add the soup and water. Sprinkle rice over and stir.
Salt and pepper chicken and place over rice mixture.
Return to oven and bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: snow white(fruity fizz, a delicate shade of pink)
directions: Whiz up plum and guava juice in a blender.
Strain into a glass and top with lemonade.
Decorate with plum slice and serve with ice.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk and mix well.
Pour over butter; do not stir. Combine peaches and remaining 1 cup sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Yields about 10 servings.

title: fried oreo cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Heat oil till hot enough to fry. Drop cookies into batter.
Drop the battered cookies into hot frying oil.
Let them get a golden brown.
Take our of oil and eat immediately.

title: chilled melon soup with berries and pine nuts
directions: Place sugar, water, vanilla bean, orange and lemon peels in a two-quart saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat for five minutes, or until a syrup consistency is obtained.
Remove from the heat; pour into a bowl and refrigerate for at least 10 minutes.

title: dressing for cabbage salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour dressing over the cabbage.
(I add a little onion and green pepper.)

title: cornflake peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, white syrup and peanut butter.
After sugar melts, remove from heat.
Add cornflakes.
Mix well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Chill.
Cut up into blocks, then serve.
A favorite with kids!

title: juanita's christmas pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly, until butter is melted.
Cool for 10 minutes or so.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually add cooled syrup to beaten eggs.
Add pecan meats.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potatoes and broccoli
directions: Whip together first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper if you wish.
Fold in French fried onions.
Spread potato mixture over bottom and up sides of a buttered 8 x 12-inch baking dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cook and drain broccoli. Arrange hot broccoli spears in potato shell.
Sprinkle cheese and remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: mk ono chocolate chip cookies
directions: * Measure oatmeal, then run it through a blender to resemble coarse flour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with butter; set aside.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine remaining ingredients.
Top with reserved cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pork chops and grilled pineapple
directions: In a dish, combine dressing, juice, sugar and soy. Add chops. Turn to coat.
Cover.
Marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 hours or overnight.
Remove chops.
Bring marinade to a boil. Grill or broil chops, basting with marinade, until done.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Brush chops generously with salad dressing.
Then coat with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° on rack in shallow pan for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Fry onion and meat in small amount of oil.
Add chili, tomato sauce and paste.
Add corn last and simmer.
Boil noodles (drain), mix noodles and meat sauce.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut cooled eggs in half lengthwise.
Place egg whites on serving plate.
Place egg yolks in mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients to yolks and mix well.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.

title: hawaiian meatballs(microwave)
directions: Mix beef, eggs, 1 tablespoon of cornstarch, onion, pepper, nutmeg, salt, garlic salt and cracker crumbs.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Place in a 4-quart shallow pan.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, rearranging once.
Drain juices.

title: rusty's texas caviar
directions: Rinse and drain peas.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill 24 hours.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix as usual.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.
Use a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Cover with icing while hot.

title: louisiana style li'l smokies
directions: Fry bacon in a large, heavy saucepan over medium heat until crisp and browned.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in pineapple juice, ketchup and sauce; mix well.
Add sausage; bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Make instant rice and set oven to 350°.
Brown ground hamburger and drain.
Add onion to hamburger and cook 5 minutes.
Add butter, soy sauce, brown sugar, drained mushrooms, soup and rice.
Add 1 cup cold water and mix.
Pour into buttered 3-quart baking dish. Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Form into round balls and drop into hot oil.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: turkish pilau
directions: Cook rice.
Melt butter or margarine.
Add onion and rice. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomato soup and diced tomatoes, shrimp, pepper and paprika.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Add a dash of cayenne pepper (to taste).
Fold in mayonnaise or salad dressing just before serving. Makes about 4 servings. Serve hot with a green salad and hot biscuits.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in greased 1-quart round casserole dish.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple beets
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Combine with a small amount of juice until it is smooth.
Add remaining juice and vinegar. Place in double boiler.
Cook until thick and clear, about 8 minutes.
Add oleo and crushed pineapple.
Drain beets.
Add to other ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese stuffed zucchini
directions: Trim ends of zucchini.

Cook in small amount of boiling salted water for 8 minutes or until just tender. Halve lengthwise. Scoop out centers and dice. Cook onion in margarine until tender. Stir in diced zucchini, cottage cheese, rice, parsley, salt and basil.

title: old-time penuche
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking until 238° on a candy thermometer, or until a small amount of mixture dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.

title: dressing for dandelion
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add milk and vinegar.
Fry bacon; add onion.
Then add all other ingredients and heat until thick.
Do not boil.
Pour over washed and dried dandelion.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Put crackers in blender and crumble.
Saute onion, butter and crackers.
In a medium bowl, mix oatmeal, cottage cheese, George Washington broth, eggs, water and breading meal.
Add cracker mixture.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add mashed bananas and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a sprayed or greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Combine chocolate cake mix, butter, water, oil and 1/2 can of condensed milk in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt and mix caramels with remaining condensed milk over low heat until smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover with remaining cake batter.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes longer or until cake tests done.
Cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in 300° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix and add flour, salt, soda and oatmeal. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Mix together dry ingredients. Add dry mixture and tomato juice to meat.
Cook slowly 3 to 4 hours.
Adding beans is optional.

title: beet pickles
directions: Tie pickling spices in a double layer of cheese cloth. Drain beets, reserving liquid in saucepan. Add sugar, vinegar and pickling spices to reserved liquid. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Pour over beets; cool. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. About 3 cups beets.

title: silver white cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 round 9-inch pans. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Beat at low speed on mixer 30 seconds.
Turning mixer on high, beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl constantly, or until batter is smooth.
Pour batter into pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 or 15 minutes before turning out to cool.

title: italian bean casserole
directions: Place alternate layers of beans, mushrooms and onion rings in a 2-quart casserole dish. Mix soup and almonds, then pour over the layers. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift together cocoa, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add egg, cream and vanilla. Beat well and bake at 350°.

title: japanese fruit cake-mom's favorite
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, coconut, jam and walnuts.
Add steamed raisins last.
Then add baking soda to buttermilk.
Alternate milk with flour to batter.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans and divide into pans evenly.
Bate at 350° until done.
Turn out on racks with wax paper to cool.
Pick up each layer carefully.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Bring to a boil 1 cup water and add butter and shortening to hot water.
Remove from heat and cool.
In a large bowl, mix eggs and sugar.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Combine this mixture and add flour.
Cover and place in refrigerator until time to use.

title: orange glazed yams
directions: Arrange yams in a single layer in a baking dish.
Brush generously with orange juice concentrate.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes, brushing frequently with juice and pan drippings until yams are well-glazed and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill 30 minutes. Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate overnight.

title: danish puff(a flaky pastry crust with a custardlike top)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup margarine into 1 cup flour until particles are size of small peas.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over flour mixture; mix.
Gather pastry into a ball; divide into halves.
Pat each half into 12 x 3-inch rectangle on ungreased cookie sheet.
Rectangles should be about 3 inches apart.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and meal.
Add flour and meal to mix.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease and fry until brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Line bottom of dish with pineapple.
Mix sugar, flour and grated cheese.
Put on top of pineapple.
Some of reserved pineapple juice may be drizzled over this mixture.
Crumble enough crackers to spread over top.
Drizzle melted butter over top of this.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven, until lightly browned. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together as usual.
Use a large bowl!
Form into golf ball size cookies and place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Makes 9 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Continue for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate. Add Marshmallow Crme, nuts and vanilla. Heat until blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9 pan. Cool. Makes 3 pounds.

title: surprise cookies
directions: Mix oleo, milk, sugar, cocoa and vanilla in saucepan and bring to a good boil.
Remove from heat and add oats and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients together in small saucepan.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice, add jello, let cool.
Add buttermilk and cool whip, stir until blended, add nuts.
Put in 8 inch pan and refrigerate.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Cook hamburger; drain grease.
Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients into saucepan or slow cooker, until cheese is well melted.
Serve with tortilla chips or use to make burritos.

title: apple and sausage omelet
directions: Melt 1 teaspoon butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add sausages and cook until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Reserve. Melt remaining butter in nonstick skillet.
Add potato and onion and cook about 5 minutes to soften.
Add apple and cook 5 more minutes, stirring occasionally with wooden spoon.
Whisk eggs, water and parsley in a bowl, reserve.
After potato mixture has cooked for 10 minutes, add oil, salt, pepper and reserved sausage. Stir and pour egg mixture into skillet.
Swirl pan so that eggs spread.
Cover skillet and cook over medium heat 15 minutes, or until eggs are set.
Remove to serving platter.
Serve immediately. Serves 2 to 4.

title: sour cream puffs
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Pat dough out on floured surface to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut into 6 to 8 biscuits. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jake's favorite fish tacos
directions: Prepare grill.
Add fish to marinade; turn to coat all sides. Set aside until grill is ready.
If using fish chunks, thread chunks on skewer.
Place fish on grill directly above coals. Grill approximately 2 minutes.
Turn and grill 2 minutes longer until fish springs back when poked.
Remove fish and set aside. If fish was cooked as a steak, break into chunks, removing all bones.
Spread fish in the middle of a warmed tortilla.
Top with fresh lime juice and tartar sauce.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Cut up fryer or parts.
Dip chicken in egg and milk.
Mix flour and cheese together and salt and pepper.
Then roll chicken in it.
Place chicken in foil-lined pan. Pour 1/2 cup melted margarine over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Take each 1/2 chicken breast and roll in dried corned beef and wrap a bacon slice around the breast.
Place side by side in baking dish and pour the sour cream and soup mixture over them. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwaved mixed veggies
directions: Melt margarine in microwave dish.
Add zucchini and microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, onion, some garlic powder and basil.
Cover and microwave until tomatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with dry cake mix. Pour melted butter on top. Top with nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: real egg rolls
directions: In 3 tablespoons oil, stir-fry bean sprouts and green onions. Simmer 10 minutes.
In a separate skillet, fry meat until it is done; drain and season to taste.
Add shrimp to meat and cook for 5 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and onion.
Mix well.
Empty mixture into a bowl.
Read back of egg roll wrappers and follow directions to prepare for filling.
Beat 1 egg.
Use this to seal egg roll after you have put filling in and rolled up.
Before rolling up, sprinkle some Cheddar cheese onto the mixture.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Split Twinkies open and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour strawberries over Twinkies.
Mix pudding according to directions on the box and pour over Twinkies.
Next the chopped nuts and top with Cool Whip.

title: favorite steak marinade
directions: Combine ingredients in a large, recloseable plastic bag with steaks (I use London Broil) and marinate in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Discard marinade and grill steak on barbecue until done to your taste.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake 25 minutes or until tops spring back.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients except the brown gravy. Make out into patties. Roll in flour and fry in small amount of hot oil until each side is lightly browned. Put in baking dish and pour the brown gravy on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add zucchini, then flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir in pineapple and raisins. Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan in order.
Do not mix.
Spread thin layer of mayo on top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Sprinkle on grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: green bean special
directions: Cook, drain and crumble wafer-thin strip of bacon.
Pour out all fat, leaving a light coating in pan.
Saute garlic, onion and pepper until onion is golden.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook gently until beans are tender (about 15 minutes).

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Add eggs, carrots, bean sprouts and onion to meat after browning.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. Separate egg roll wrap.
Use a teaspoon to fill wraps.
Close ends and roll together.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: grits casserole
directions: Stir all together well and bake 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: ham and cheese on a bun
directions: Grate ham (or cut into small cubes); grate cheese.
Mix together.
(You can add some mayonnaise, if you'd like.) Spoon mixture onto buns.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to melt cheese.
Really yummy!

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Place all ingredients except 1/2 cup chocolate chips into bowl and mix until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until center is puffed and dry. Spread remaining 1/2 cup over top.
Wait 3 or 4 minutes until melted, then spread evenly.

title: dogs in yellow snow
directions: In bowl mix franks, potatoes, egg and 1 cup of grated cheese. Put in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until light brown.
Remove from oven and top with remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese.

title: terry's potatoes
directions: Melt stick of butter in microwave.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour butter over potatoes evenly.
Mix in sour cream, soup and cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: apple pudding pie
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add beaten egg and then add sifted flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix.
Add chopped apples and nuts.
Continue beating after apples are added and when well mixed.
Place in buttered pie plate and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: favorite chicken breasts
directions: Stir sauce and soup together, mixing well.
Place pieces of ham on chicken breast and roll up, holding in place with a toothpick.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Serve with rice.
(The sauce makes wonderful gravy.)

title: betty jo's pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Gradually add flour, buttermilk and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix well about 3 minutes. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: carrot choppers salad
directions: Boil sliced carrots in salted water about 10 minutes.
Mix next 6 ingredients well and pour over drained carrots.
Add peppers and onions.
Put in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: pool cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well, then add flour and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Take a spoonful of pie filling and make little pools in cake until all the pie filling is used.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when still warm.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and butter well.
Add sugar gradually; mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup milk alternating.
Mix well.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat 1 minute each; mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup milk; mix well.
Grease and flour cake mold.
Put in cold oven, then turn on to 325° and bake for 1 hour. Turn oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas(serving size:  15; mexican)
directions: Cook meat and onion until meat is brown; drain off any excess fat.
Add salt and taco sauce; stir until blended.
Dip tortillas in hot oil; fry quickly until limp.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon equal portions of the meat mixture onto tortillas.
Top each with 1 tablespoon of Monterey Jack cheese.
Roll up; place seam-side down in a lightly greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter; add flour and bouillon granules, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add water.
Cook, stirring often, until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and chilies.
Pour mixture over rolled tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Butter on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour to blend flavors.
Yields 10 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes in preheated oven.

title: light carob truffles
directions: *Coconut sugar is made with 1 1/4 cups unsweetened flaked coconut.
In a food processor, process coconut until the consistency of powdered sugar.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine cooked spaghetti noodles with Italian dressing and Supreme seasoning.
Mix in all chopped vegetables.
Evenly distribute them throughout the noodles.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Before serving, mix/stir salad again to ensure that dressing is mixed in well and noodles are thoroughly coated

title: sausage balls
directions: After grating cheese, let stand until pliable.
Add Bisquick mix, sausage and salt.
Mix by hand and shape into small balls. Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes about 50.
May be frozen, but should be thawed before cooking.

title: easy lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, egg and Cool Whip until it becomes thick batter.
Roll by tablespoon in powdered sugar.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vinegar pie (pecan)
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo; beat in 1 cup sugar.
Add 2 eggs and beat again.
Add 3 teaspoons vinegar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat again.
Fold in 2/3 cup pecans.
Bake in frozen pie shell 30 minutes at 350°.

title: instant russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a jar.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Place individual baking liners in muffin pan.
Fill cup 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with the sugar.
Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture in cake batter.
Bake as cake directs.

title: pea salad
directions: Blanch peas for 1 minute and drain.
Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Combine peas, peanuts, onions, celery and bacon in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and Italian dressing together.
Pour over vegetables and toss.

title: delicious corn bread
directions: Pour boiling water over blended shortening and 1 cup cornmeal and stir briskly. Sift together 1 cup cornmeal, soda, salt and baking powder. Blend together buttermilk and eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients to milk and eggs mixture.
Then add to first mixture and mix thoroughly. Have greased 13 x 9 pan piping hot and bake 25 to 30 minutes in 425° to 450° oven.

title: deluxe pineapple meat loaf
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Add 1 tablespoon catsup to reserved juice and set aside.
Drain rest of pineapple and add to remaining ingredients.
Mix together well.
Pour in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with pineapple juice catsup mixture.
Return to oven for an additional 15 minutes.

title: carrot hash browns
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and oil.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions.
Add seasonings.
Saute until browned on one side.
Flip over and saute on second side until browned.
Break apart into small chunks or serve in wedges cut from the round.

title: herb tea
directions: Brew as usual for approximately 10 minutes.
(Steep in water that has been brought to a boil.)
Strain and add water to make 1 gallon.
Sweeten to taste with sugar or honey.

title: super slaw
directions: In large glass or plastic bowl, combine Super Slaw mix, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Add 8 to 9 cups (about 1 1/2 pounds) shredded cabbage; toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until serving time or overnight.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, carrots and celery in oil until soft. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, wine and seasonings. Let come to a soft boil and simmer 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Combine egg and apple juice. Stir into dry ingredients. Fold in 1 cup apple, raisins, walnuts and cherries. Pour into a greased 8 x 4 x 2 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring often, for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until desired consistency is reached.
Serve over hot spaghetti.
Top with grated cheese.

title: mexican style potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into cubes.
Place in medium saucepan with water; cook until done.
Drain and cool.
Combine oil, vinegar, chili powder and seasoned salt; blend well.
Add all remaining ingredients, except potatoes.
Mix well.
Fold in potatoes. Cover; refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Two cups of marshmallow cream may be used.)

title: jeano's italian casserole
directions: Remove skin and brown sausages; slice and set aside.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and salt.
Saute onion in a little olive oil; add broccoli, mushrooms and garlic salt.
Cook until glazed.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Mix bacon, cream cheese, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: rice and broccoli
