directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Mix
entire
bottle of chili sauce and can of cranberry sauce. Cook
over
medium
heat.
Slowly bring the sauce to a boil. Simmer hot dogs in sauce until cooked thoroughly.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla. Beat until combined. Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add boiling water; mix well.
Cook until thick.
Add oleo and vanilla.

title: apple pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Make a batter of these in blender or food processor.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy cast-iron skillet.
Pour batter into skillet and put on top rack of oven. Bake until edges are brown and crisp, about 20 minutes.
Meantime, quarter, core and peel apples.
Thinly slice them.
Heat remaining butter in another large skillet.
Add apple slices; sprinkle with sugar and saute over high heat until apples are browned.
Spread over pancake, and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan (glass is best).

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Combine all ingredients.
The amount of vinegar may be adjusted to suit the taste.
I add a couple of packages of Sweet 'N Low also.

title: sauerkraut surprise cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mix, alternating with water.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Pour into 2 round or square pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool. Frost.
May be topped with nuts or coconut.

title: lemon cheese bundt cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs, 1 cup flour and 1 cup of sugar.
Mix on low speed until blended.
Repeat until all ingredients are blended.
Add extracts and blend well. Pour batter into a prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Puree all ingredients and bring to a slow boil.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Put in jars and process.
Makes about 18 pints. Excellent on pizza and stuffed peppers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss in bread cubes in melted margarine until coated.
Sprinkle cooked sausage and grated Cheddar cheese over bread.
Combine milk, eggs and dry mustard.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serves 8 hungry beachcombers along with fresh fruit and beverage.

title: salad bowl jello
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Layer half of jello; let set until firm.
Pour on sour cream, then the rest of jello mix.
Chill until firm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Alternate layers of vegetables, soup and eggs.
Place small amount of margarine on each layer.
Crumble cheese crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes in casserole dish and top with soup and cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cream filled ice cream pie
directions: Mix cookies and butter; press in bottom of 12-inch pie taker. Spread ice cream over top of cookies.
Pour fudge topping in an even layer over ice cream.
Spread whipped topping over fudge. Put in freezer for at least 2 hours.
Good overnight.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400° (375° if using glass dish).
Saute onions and parsley in butter.
Add shrimp and seasonings; cook until shrimp turn pink.
Lightly grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Sprinkle cheese in plate.
Drain shrimp, reserving liquid.
Add shrimp to cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 6 large servings.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine in a buttered baking dish with 1 cup grated Longhorn cheese.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and pineapple juice.
Pour over tidbits and cheese.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup to 1 cup bread crumbs and dot with butter (1/4 cup).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: canadian bacon with sauteed peaches
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add peaches, brown sugar and spices.
Cook until glazed.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, flour and water.
Cook until thick and smooth; stir constantly.
While hot stir in butter and lemon extract.
Pour into baked pie shell and sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Cool before serving.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook water and rice until done.
Drain.
Add milk and butter; cook 1 hour at 350°.
(Add raisins.)
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir into rice; cook 15 more minutes.
Let cool.

title: lattice top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spread mixture into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine biscuit mix, egg and milk to form a soft dough.
Spoon in lattice design over hot chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions and bake 3 to 5 minutes longer until cheese melts and onions are lightly browned.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix your biscuit dough like always and use baked sweet potatoes.
Peel the sweet potatoes and mix in your biscuit dough. Judge the amount, you may need more than one potato if potato is small.
You will probably have to add some flour after mixing the sweet potato in the biscuit dough.
Then roll the dough out and cut into biscuits and bake.
Ready when starting to brown lightly.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix and sprinkle in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan coconut and chopped pecans.

title: tasty stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Set stems aside.
In large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Saute mushroom caps on bottom side only for 3 to 4 minutes.
Arrange mushroom caps in shallow baking dish with rounded side down.
Chop green pepper, onion and mushroom stems by hand or in food processor until very fine.
Heat remaining margarine in skillet; saute chopped stems, pepper and onion until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Fill caps with this mixture, mounding high in center. Bake 15 minutes.
Serve as appetizer or as side dish.

title: sister mary augusta's cinnamon buns
directions: Cream sugar and Spry or Crisco.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add salt, potatoes and potato water.
Mix well.
Add 4 cups of flour and dry yeast; mix well.
Add 4 more cups flour.
Knead.
Add enough flour to stiffen and does not stick (can be a lot of flour) to fingers.
Place in warm place until double in bulk (2 1/2 to 3 hours).
Take portion, roll and spread with butter or oleo; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll as you do a jellyroll. Cut in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in buttered pans that have the following mixture in them.

title: charlie the tuna in a blanket
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Split buns and fill.
Heat wrapped in foil in slow 250° oven for about 30 minutes or until filling is bubbly and cheese is melted.
Great with chips and hot chocolate.

title: sister marshall's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients in skillet.
Add milk, stirring constantly, on medium heat.
Cook unti gravy thickens and bubbles.
Scrape bottom of pan often.
Pour over hot biscuits.

title: mustard coated rib roast
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Mix mustard, onion and garlic in another bowl.
Rub mustard mixture onto meat.
Sprinkle with spice mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Allow meat to stand 2 hours at room temperature.
Roast at 350° for about 45 minutes for medium.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: brownies and hot fudge sauce
directions: Don't mix in mixer.
Melt chocolate squares in butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and stir well. Add dry ingredients and stir well. Then add eggs and vanilla.
Can add nuts if you wish.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low for 2 hours. Let set overnight if possible in refrigerator. Reheat next day for approximately 2 hours.

title: strawberry jello bake
directions: Place strawberries in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry jello on top.
Mix together sugar, flour and butter or oleo and spread on top of the berries.
Bake until crust is brown and fruit is soft, about an hour at 350°.
Top with whipped cream.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix all together except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: kolach - potato bread(filling only)
directions: Cut cheese into small pieces and set aside.
Beat eggs in another bowl and set aside.
Mince onions and fry in margarine until brown.

title: rhubarb jello jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand overnight.
In morning, add jello.
Heat to boiling and boil 1 minute.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Uses lots of rhubarb in short time.

title: pineapple banana punch
directions: Blend bananas with juices in blender, half at a time.
Add water and sugar (dissolve together first).
Blend well.
Put mixture in freezable plastic containers (2 to 4, depending on size).
Freeze well.
Approximately 2 hours before serving, remove containers from freezer and place in refrigerator.
Put into punch bowl and add 50/50.
Will make 2 full punch bowls.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix 4 tablespoons salt with the ground cucumbers.
Mix 1 tablespoon salt with the ground onions.
Let these mixtures stand 2 hours.
Drain well; press to remove excess liquid.

title: yellow angel cake
directions: Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl until foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Beat egg yolks in small bowl of electric mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Add cold water and continue beating until thick.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
Add sugar, gradually beating until blended.
Add vanilla, almond and lemon extracts.
Fold in flour and salt.
Fold beaten egg whites into egg yolk mixture.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan in 325° oven for 1 hour, or until done.
Invert to cool.
Frost with Creamy Yellow Frosting.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; remove part of drippings.
Thicken drippings with 2 tablespoons flour.
Add vinegar, sugar and water.
Pour over potatoes, onion and hard-cooked egg.
Simmer together a few minutes.
(My family prefers a mild salad, so I use the cheapest vinegar I can find.)

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Heat to boiling butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Add flour, sugar and soda and mix gently.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: quick and easy lower fat cakes
directions: Spray desired size pans with cooking spray.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions with the following modifications: add 1 tablespoon flour to dry mix and stir well, substitute an equal amount of applesauce for the vegetable oil.
Bake and cool as directed.
Frost with your favorite light frosting.

title: apple cheese fruit salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Add salad dressing and stir gently.
Add orange sections.
Toss.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese danish
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Spread 1 can rolls on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 1/4 cup of sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread on top of roll layer.
Layer other can of rolls on top of mixture.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and let set overnight.

title: yum cake
directions: Bake and cool 1 large white or yellow cake mix.
Prepare 3 ounces vanilla pudding mix; spread over cake.
Put 1 can drained, crushed pineapple over pudding.
Spread 1 large bowl of Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top.

title: oriental salad
directions: Brown together oleo, sliced almonds, sesame seeds, Ramen noodles.
Boil for one minute vinegar, oil, sugar and soy sauce. Cool then mix with browned ingredients and cabbage and green onions.

title: cauliflower lettuce salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Spread mayonnaise over layer.
Sprinkle the sugar over top.
Seal in Tupperware bowl and let stand overnight. Toss before serving.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, flour and oatmeal together.
Mix well. Place half of the mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pat out to make crust.
Spread pie filling over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crust mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili dog volcano
directions: Split hot dog lengthwise.
Open the bun and place each half of the hot dog on each half of the bun.
Cover hot dog and bun with Fritos, making a mound of chips in the middle to resemble a volcano.
Cover chips, bun and hot dog with chili.
Sprinkle with onions and cover entire concoction with shredded cheese. Microwave until cheese is melted and chili is hot.
Melted cheese will resemble hot lava running down volcano.
Be careful; it's very hot.
Enjoy!

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan on medium heat.
Add onion; cook and stir 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add flour; cook 1 minute or until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until Velveeta is melted and soup is heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes in jacket; put in large casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle cubed cheese over the potatoes, then onion, pimento, parsley, paprika and garlic salt.
Melt margarine; add bread crumbs and pour over the entire casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pizzelles
directions: Melt butter and Crisco, cool.
Beat eggs until foamy, add sugar and beat.
Add vanilla, anise and lemon juice.
Add about 6 to 7 cups flour.
Heat pizzelle iron and drop mixture by teaspoon onto hot iron.
This recipe makes a great big batch of pizzelles.

title: mexican soup(low-fat)
directions: Cook all ingredients in crock-pot or on stove on medium heat for 1 hour.
Before serving, add 1 package dry Ranch dressing. Stir well and cook a little longer.

title: sunday school bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine salt, sugar and margarine in 1 cup boiling water; mix well until margarine is melted.
Add 1 cup cold water, eggs, yeast mixture and part of flour.
Beat well, add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead. Place dough in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape as desired.
Let rise while you go to Sunday School (about 1 hour). Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 15 rolls or 1 loaf.

title: microwave cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Cook 3 1/2 minutes. Stir.
Cook 3 1/2 more minutes.
Stir until thick.
(Sometimes you may need to cook 1 more minute.)

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese get soft by setting out for 1 hour.
Mix in shrimp, green pepper and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead ingredients together with hands until well blended. Shape into walnut size balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat slowly while adding onions and peppers until meat is brown.
Add tomato sauce and spices; heat.
Place a layer of tortillas in bottom of a large casserole dish, then a layer of meat, one of cheese, tortillas until casserole is full.
Cover with soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: scalloped potato bake
directions: Spread 4 cups sliced potatoes in bottom of greased 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine onion, soups, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour half the mixture over potatoes.
Repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: chess pie
directions: Soften butter.
Add sugar and mix eggs and corn meal.
Mash up with fork.
Slowly add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pepped up dipping sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in small saucepan; cook over medium heat until hot.
Serve with warm breadsticks.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter and margarine in saucepan.
Add Worcestershire, black pepper, rosemary, lemon juice, salt and garlic to butter mixture.

title: polk-barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer half an hour.
To vary, cook 1 grated onion and 1 minced clove of garlic 5 minutes in butter and add to the sauce.

title: okra fingers
directions: Wash okra.
Trim the stems.
Drain well and place in a shallow container.
Pour buttermilk over the okra.
Set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese and leave out of refrigerator for 1 hour.
Mix with all other ingredients, except pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans and refrigerate in plastic wrap.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in a baking dish; add water to 1-inch of top.
Mix sugars and flour together.
Place over top of sweet potatoes.
Cut margarine or butter in pieces.
Put evenly over top of sugar.
Add vanilla evenly over top.
Sprinkle spices over top. For more rich flavor add a tablespoon of evaporated milk.
Bake in microwave on High about 5 minutes, then put in regular oven and bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 325° to 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool slightly and roll in powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt; stir in rhubarb.
Put in a 9-inch pie pan and dot with butter.
Add top and bake like apple pie.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and confectioners sugar thoroughly.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press mixture evenly into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients, spread over baked layer.
Bake 20 minutes. Cool, cut into bars.
Tastes just like pecan pie.

title: herbed salmon steaks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Place frozen fish steaks in pan.
Mix lemon juice, marjoram leaves, onion salt and seasoned peppers; spoon on fish.

title: miracle whip wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Place drinking glass in center of serving platter.
Drop mixture to form ring around glass; smooth with spatula.
Remove glass.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Serve with Triscuits or crackers of your choice.

title: gourmet garlic bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough red wine to make a paste mixture.
Spread on slices of French or Italian bread.
Sprinkle with paprika and broil until bubbly and golden brown.
It's great with spaghetti or even all by itself.

title: nacho taco dip
directions: Mix taco mix with refried beans.
Spread in dish.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips.

title: portuguese rice pudding
directions: Boil together until cooked to look like paste.
Add 2 eggs into cooked mixture and heat well all together.
Add a little vanilla.
Put on large plate or platter and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: frances ferrell's chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large Dutch oven.
Cover with cold water. Add spices and simmer until done and chicken falls from bone, about 4 hours.
Remove chicken and bring broth to a rolling boil. Put flour in bowl and add 1 cup broth.
Stir to make a dough. Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips and add to boiling broth.
After all dough is added, put chicken into pot and stir to mix.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Pour all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
When mixture reaches a full, rolling boil, time it for 5 minutes.
Test drops in cold water to see if they form a ball.
Pour into a buttered pan and let cool.
This fudge is more like taffy.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally across into thin slices, then cut strips about 2-inches long.
Heat corn oil in skillet.
Place garlic clove in oil.
Remove after 3 minutes.
Add meat to oil.
Cook on medium heat; turn as needed until brown.
Mix onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and ginger.
Cook on medium.
Stir until just tender (3 minutes).
Blend cornstarch with steak and soy sauce.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring, until thickened.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and chocolate.
Add sugar; beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into well greased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool cake in pan and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: pop's apple ugly cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients, then, stir in the wet look: oil, eggs and vanilla, and for the rugged, chunky taste, mix in apples and raisins.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Mix well and put in a baking dish.
Top with butter, cornflakes and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May cook celery and onions in butter before adding.

title: millon dollar pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour and mix just until blended after each addition. Stir in extracts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 40 minutes or until cake tests done (cake will rise above the pan during baking, but will settle while cooling).
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: hot fruit tea
directions: Bring to a boil and then simmer.

title: wassail punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, sugar and water.
Stir to dissolve sugar and heat to boiling.
Tie spices into a cheesecloth bag. Add to
liquid and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Just before serving, add frozen juices and pineapple juice.
Serve steaming hot.
Makes about 1 gallon.
I serve this in mugs.

title: double cheese delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute mushrooms and onions.
Brown hamburg and drain.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and cottage cheese.
Add tomato sauce to mushrooms, onions and hamburg.
Add cheese mixture to hamburg mixture.
Keep heated on very low temperature.
Cook noodles for casserole.
Place drained noodles in casserole dish.
Stir in hamburg mixture.
Bake covered for 30 minutes.

title: bargain cheese
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Let it cool a wee bit.
Add mayonnaise and horseradish.
Mix well.
Put in pots in refrigerator.
Will keep for months in sealed crock-pots in refrigerator.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and place in ovensafe dish.
Mix together sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Add cheese, crushed crackers and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garbanzos and rice
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Add juice from the cans of beans and immediately add 1 well beaten egg and stir until congealing; add beans and chicken seasoning for taste.

title: pound cake #1
directions: Cream
sugar and Crisco; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly	after
each
addition.	Add flour; mix thoroughly. Add lemon
juice
and	vanilla.
Add
a
few drops of milk if needed for mixing.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine;
add
cocoa,
sugar,
vanilla, milk and eggs. Beat until
mixed.
Do
not
overbeat.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake
10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes. Pie
is
done
when
springs up in center of pie. Quick and easy. Children love this pie.
Can be frozen.
Heat in microwave; place a dip of ice cream on top.

title: chocolate creme filled cupcakes
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and baking powder.
Mix in vanilla, salad oil, sugar, salt, hot coffee and egg yolks.

title: almejas con arroz(clams with rice)
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in olive oil until onion is soft. Add rice; stir to glaze.
Add stock or bouillon, saffron, tomatoes, salt and clams with juice; bring to a boil.
Cook uncovered 15 minutes; add chopped olives.
Cover; let stand in warm place 10 to 15 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed and rice fluffy or can be placed in 300° oven.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar and salt, then add butter.
Mix the flour and baking powder together.
Add the flour to the eggs and milk; mix well.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and cool.

title: elsie's dinner rolls
directions: Mix together warm water and yeast.
Add rest of ingredients. Knead and let rise until double.
Butter your hands; place in buttered pan.
Let rise again and bake at 325° until brown.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with the margarine.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 3 minutes.
Cool and press dry.
Finely chop the broccoli in a food processor.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Thoroughly mix flour, baking powder, and salt. Stir into egg mixture, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese, and onion.
Spoon into baking dish, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Let stand for 5 minutes and then cut into bite-size pieces.
Makes 4 dozen (1 1/2 inch) squares.

title: baked clam dip(makes 2 quiche dishes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in pan.
Place chopped onion and garlic in butter. Let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: puppy chow(for chocolate lovers, not puppies)
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl; set aside.
Microwave chocolate chips, peanut butter, and margarine in a 1 quart microwavable bowl on high 1 minute; stir.
Microwave 30 seconds longer or until mixture can be stirred smooth.
Stir in vanilla. Pour chocolate mixture over cereal in bowl, stirring until evenly coated.
Pour into large plastic food storage bag.	Add powdered sugar.
Seal bag; shake until well-coated.	Spread on wax paper to cool.
Yield: 9 cups of snack.

title: dumplings
directions: Drop in boiling broth and cook with lid on for 15 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Beat ingredients together and spread over cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Let set until firm.

title: cheese squash
directions: Place squash in 2 to 3-quart pan to boil.
Add salt to boil. Boil until soft, about 20 minutes.
Pour off water.
Add cheese to taste, 5 to 6 chunks, stir until melted.

title: plantain chips
directions: Peel plantain and diagonally cut into 1/8-inch thick slices. Combine 1 quart water and 1 tablespoon salt in a large bowl, stirring until salt dissolves; add plantain slices. Cover and let stand 30 minutes. Drain plantain slices well and pat dry. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet; add plantain slices and cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until tender, but not brown. Drain well on paper towels.

title: quick tater casserole
directions: Mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 426° for one hour.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Spread diced rhubarb evenly in bottom of a 7 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 cup of sugar and Jell-O powder over the top, then the Jiffy cake mix.
Pour the hot water over the contents and drizzle the margarine.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
May be served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat last four ingredients.
Add to the vegetables and chill.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 3 hours at 325°.

title: three layer salad
directions: Spread a layer of Cool Whip on jello.
Mix pudding and spread on Cool Whip.
Decorate with nuts or coconut or colored cherries. Can be used as a dessert.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and taco mix.
Layer ingredients as listed. When ready to serve, add meat and sour cream and toss together.

title: bisquick "corny" bread sticks
directions: Mix Bisquick, corn and sugar.
Roll out to medium thickness; will rise.
Dough is sticky.
Sprinkle surface lightly with flour as needed and pat out with hands on floured surface (works better than rolling pin).
Cut into strips similar to chicken pastry dough.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a large oven roaster or similar pan.
Remove from oven and lay strips of dough (about size of 2 fingers) in melted butter.
Dough is still rather difficult to work with but have patience; some folks think it's worth the effort! Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn all pieces over and bake 5 to 10 minutes more, until golden brown.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple cooler
directions: Combine buttermilk, sugar and pineapple juice.
Add sugar to taste; chill thoroughly and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: special chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and bone.
Layer chicken in dish; layer boiled eggs, sliced.
Pour green peas over chicken and eggs, then pour melted margarine over peas.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick with 1 cup milk and pour over contents with 2 cups chicken broth and 1 can celery soup, mixed well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: o'henry bars
directions: Heat syrup, sugar and peanut butter until peanut butter melts, stirring all the time.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Add nuts; stir until well mixed.
Pat out into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Mix vegetables, onions, water chestnuts, cheese and mayonnaise.
Pour into a 9-inch square dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with crushed crackers that have been mixed in the melted butter.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Very good!

title: melt in your mouth chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bring to a boil chicken broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Combine other ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: lemon or banana pound cake
directions: Beat everything on high speed about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
(You can use butter or margarine.) Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cake is done when you press the middle down with finger and it springs back up.
Either banana or lemon is made the same.
If you can't get the matching instant pudding, you can always use vanilla instant pudding.
The corresponding pudding makes a better cake.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Pour ingredients into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then add meringue and brown.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Prepare jello per package.
Add softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir. Pour into Pyrex dish and chill overnight.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Salt, pepper and flour each slice. Lightly brown in corn oil.
Place in greased casserole dish.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Mix all but last ingredient in a large bowl.
Place broken pretzels in 9 x 13-inch baking pan, stir mixture onto pretzels until all pieces are coated.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, turn once.

title: hot spiced fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 1/2 cup combined syrup.
Arrange fruit in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine rest of the ingredients, except butter.
Pour over fruits.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm topped with sour cream sauce.

title: bacon and potato salad
directions: Fry the bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Leave aside.
Scrub the red potatoes and boil until tender.
Cube potatoes.
Add bacon, mayonnaise and parsley; mix.
Salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Beat 4 egg whites.
Add cream of tartar and 1 cup sugar slowly.
Bake at 300° 1 hour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Beat 4 egg yolks.
Add lemon juice, rind and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add water if too thick.
Add lemon mixture over meringue.
Spread with 1/2 pint whipped cream.

title: quick and easy cream cheese pie
directions: Place cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk in bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add lemon juice.
Blend well.
Fill pie crust with mixture and smooth.
Place tinfoil over top and place in freezer 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Enjoy!

title: tamale pie
directions: For Cornmeal Crust:
Put first 4 ingredients into a 2 or 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Cover with a paper plate and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
After first 4 minutes, stir every 2 minutes.
Let set 20 to 30 minutes to cool enough to handle, then line a greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Form crust.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower. Cook or steam whole until tender.
Heat mayonnaise, salt and mustard.
Frost over evenly the tips of the cauliflower. Top with cheese.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: saucy baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients together and bake uncovered at 300° for 3 to 5 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef barbecue(when it's dad's turn to cook, this is it!)
directions: Cook the chuck or arm roast in pressure cooker or crock-pot until meat falls apart.
Shred with fork; return to pan, saving juices.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and heat through.
Serve on buns.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add sugar.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time, blending well.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in oats and vanilla.
Bake in greased 9-inch square pan in preheated 350° oven.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut while warm.

title: double chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with mixture of milk and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Spread frosting over cake.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Add rice; mix well.
Add beef consomme and onion soup.
Add water.
Cover with foil; bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine powdered sugar, orange juice and margarine.
Blend in vanilla wafers and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate for several hours then shape into small bowls and roll in coconut or chopped nuts.

title: creamed hamburger on potatoes
directions: Brown beef; add onions and cook until done.
Add soup and soy sauce.
Serve over potatoes.

title: john's crab meat dip
directions: Blend sherry a little at a time into cream cheese until smooth. Add balance of ingredients.
Heat.
Serve warm.
This is good
heated in a fondue pot.

title: hungry man's pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in frying pan.
Add salt.
In a large saucepan, combine undiluted soup and tomatoes.
Add ground beef mixture and cook slowly about 1 hour.
Cook noodles; drain.
In a 2-quart greased casserole, put a layer of noodles; cover with meat sauce and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In food processor, process oats until powdered.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Process briefly to blend.

title: auntie betty's chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, shortening and salt in double boiler over hot water.
Beat eggs until thickened.
Gradually add sugar until golden color.
Mix in rolled oats and vanilla.
Mix well. Let mix cool completely.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie tin.
Bake in 350° oven until the cookies appear dry.
Do not overbake.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Pour off fat but save remaining liquid.
Add deboned chicken to liquid.
Add soup.
Add butter.
Cut up tortillas into 2-inch squares.
Add tortillas to mixture.
Cook about 30 minutes or until dumplings are tender.

title: strawberry bread with strawberry cream cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Make a well in center of flour mixture.
Pour strawberries, oil, egg white and pecans into well. Mix well.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely on rack.
Combine cream cheese and reserved strawberry juice.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: ricotta puffs
directions: Combine Ricotta with beaten eggs and sugar.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Gradually add Ricotta mixture.
Stir in brandy.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Drop by teaspoon in hot deep fat at 375° and brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with dusted confectioners sugar or mix cinnamon and sugar and roll in mixture.

title: malted milk squares
directions: In medium saucepan, mix together gelatine, sugar and cocoa. Blend in egg yolks, beaten, with milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into bowl.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: magic beef stew
directions: Clean and cut up vegetables.
In large Dutch oven, layer first 5 ingredients.
Combine salt, pepper, sugar and tapioca; sprinkle over vegetables.
Combine tomato juice and water; pour over all. Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: granny's tater soup
directions: Place all ingredients (except milk and chives) in a 4-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours. Stir in milk and chives during the last hour of cooking. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Shred imitation crab.
Mix onions, pepper and celery with imitation crab.
Dilute approximately 1/4 cup mayonnaise with lemon juice to form a creamy substance.
Incorporate into all ingredients.
Ingredient amounts may be increased or decreased to individual taste.

title: molasses filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured board. Cut dough with round cookie cutter about 2 inches in diameter.
On bottom part of cookie, place about 1 teaspoon of filling with little of liquid portion.
Slash top of cookie to about 1/4 inch from sides.
Pull back and place over bottom part and filling. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: simple scalloped potatoes
directions: In greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole, arrange sliced potatoes. Add flour, salt and pepper; toss lightly.
Stir in milk and dot with butter.
Cook, covered with lid, 15 minutes or until potatoes are desired doneness.
Stir 3 to 4 times during cooking.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
(Can use onions.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked tagliarini
directions: Brown onions, green peppers, garlic and hamburger until tender and meat crumbles. Add to cooked spaghetti and mix.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add corn and olives along with grated cheese.
Place in casserole.
Top with a little additional grated cheese, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Can use shredded Cheddar or Mozzarella cheese on top of vegetables.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add oatmeal and walnuts.
Mix well. Form into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill cookie mix.
Slice and bake at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix in soup.
Cube cheese; add to mixture.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in boiling water for 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in sugar and flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until boiling.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in nuts, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cover with a top crust which has slots cut in it.
Bake until brown at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: I stew a couple of chicken breasts (or you can use store bought roasted chicken) so chicken is flavorful and tender.

title: senator salad
directions: Drain beans, peas and pimentos.
Combine with celery, green pepper and onion.
Heat first four ingredients.
Let cool.
Pour all together and store in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a foil-lined flower pot.

title: cheerios cookies
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat the sugar and syrup.
Add peanut butter, mixing well.
Remove from heat.
Add the Cheerios. Stir and drop on waxed paper by a teaspoon.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1/3 cup milk and caramels and heat until melted.
Combine cake mix (while caramels melt) with butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Put 1/2 of mix in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down.
Bake 6 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and press down.
Pour caramel mix over this and sprinkle with remaining cake mixture.
Bake 18 minutes and allow to sit at least 6 hours (preferably overnight).
This freezes well and tastes great frozen.

title: crock-pot beef roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides.
Place potatoes, carrots, onion and mushroom soup in bottom of pot.
Add salt, pepper and water. Place roast on top.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: joy's banana nut bread
directions: 1. Mix the above.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts. 2. Spoon into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 50-60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes two loaves.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add the rest of the ingredients, beating slowly until mixed. Fry on a flat griddle, making sure it is completely filled with dough.

title: puff pastry tartlets
directions: Lightly roll out puff pastry and cut into desired rounds (2 inch diameter minimum).
With tines of fork, liberally poke pastry.
Place puff rounds on parchment lined cookie sheet. Arrange sun-dried tomatoes and olives in decorative pattern and crumble Feta cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 - 20 minutes until cheese is bubbly and pastry is golden brown.
Top with fresh basil that has been finely shredded/chopped.
Drizzle with olive oil and serve immediately.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Defrost broccoli.
Press to remove excess moisture.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole, combine margarine and onion.
Microwave until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients except broccoli.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally.
Add broccoli.
Microwave until heated through, stirring once.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: healthy lemon pie(sugar-free)
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk; whip until thick and add 1 tub Crystal Light, stirring well.
Fold in 2 containers of whipped topping.
Pour mixture into 2 graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in a greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: sauteed roma tomatoes with mushrooms
directions: Cut tomatoes into uniform wedges, halve mushrooms, finely chop garlic, coarsely chop the mint leaves.
Halve, peel and thinly slice the red onion.
Close to serving time, heat pan over high flame.
Add olive oil and swirl.
Quickly add onions and saute 4 to 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until liquid is absorbed, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and garlic.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add wine, salt and pepper.
Cook no more than a minute. Remove from heat and stir in cheese and mint.
Serves 8.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna.
Combine mushroom soup, onion, chicken broth, wine, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring sauce to a boil and add diced chicken, broccoli, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Mix marinara sauce and orange peel.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 cup nuts for outside. Mix well.
Roll in remaining nuts; form ball and chill.
Makes 1 large ball.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix and chill. Makes 2 cups.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Bring margarine, Coca-Cola and cocoa to boil. Remove from heat. Add powdered sugar and nuts. Spread icing on cake while hot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken in dish, then layer cooked broccoli, followed by mixture of soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chew bars
directions: Sift salt, baking powder and flour into mixing bowl.
Add sifted brown sugar, granulated sugar, chocolate, dates and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Whip in well beaten eggs.
Line an 8 x 8-inch pan with waxed paper; grease well and spread mixture in it. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Cut into bars while hot and when cool, remove from pan.
Store in an airtight box.
Makes 32 (1 x 2-inch) bars.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat butter with an electric mixer at low speed until smooth and creamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Mix in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, beating 3 to 5 minutes after each addition.
Spoon into baked pie shell. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Top with whipped cream and pecans.

title: make-ahead breakfast
directions: Spread bread crumbs in a buttered dish.
Brown sausage and drain.
Put sausage over bread; top with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan until well separated. Transfer to 3-quart saucepan.
Cook onion, pepper and garlic cloves in same frying pan.
Add to ground beef in saucepan.
Add salt and pepper to ground beef.
Add soup (undiluted) and cook over low heat several hours, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms just before serving.
Serve over thin spaghetti and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: lit'l cornbread wraps
directions: Separate dough into sixteen strips; cut each strip in half. Wrap dough around links and press ends together to seal.
Bake as directed on dough package.

title: cornish pastry(south english traditional dish)
directions: Roll pastry 1/4-inch thick.
Keep portion as round as possible (approximately 10-inch diameter).
Pile mixture in center of pastry round.
Wet edges and join them together on the top to form a frill; prick with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook for approximately 50 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp and pastain butter sauce
directions: Cook pasta.
Combine butter, water, oil, parsley, garlic and salt in large skillet.
Heat on medium setting until boiling.
Add shrimp and cook 5 to 7 minutes until shrimp are bright pink.
Pour sauce over cooked spaghetti and linguine.
Add Parmesan cheese. Serve.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples and fill a 9 x 13 x 2-inch-baking dish.
Top each quarter with a small amount of margarine.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Slowly add water to dish to a 1/2-inch depth.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until apples are done. Serves 12.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and mayo.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and place on top of cream cheese and mayo mixture. Serve with nacho chips.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Layer hash browns, cheese, salt, pepper, onion and bell pepper in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle on cooked meat. Mix eggs and milk; pour over all. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cut in squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients with banana; mix well.
Add walnuts and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf or 3 mini loaves.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Alternate meat, onion, tomatoes and green pepper on skewers. Mix remaining ingredients and brush on kabobs.
Cook on grill or broil to desired doneness.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cheddar cheese potatoes
directions: Use only milk for portion for water and milk on instructions on box of instant potatoes.
Add sour cream and softened cream cheese. Mix in Cheddar cheese and seasonings.
This can be mixed in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lentil salad *
directions: Put lentils in large kettle and cover with water 2 inches above bean level.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Drain in colander and rinse in cold water.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Add to cooled lentils.
Then add parsley and onion slices as a garnish.

title: sauteed chicken in cream sauce
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add chicken and vegetables and seasonings.
Cook over medium heat stirring occasionally 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add 2 tablespoons wine and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, milk and remaining wine in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth. Place noodles on platter.
Top with chicken mixture and cream cheese mixture.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Let dough thaw and raise. Put in a greased circle pan (pizza pan works good). Mix together cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla. Spread over bread dough. Mix together butter, sugar, flour and crumble together. Pour topping over filling and let rise 30-45 minutes. Bake 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to box.
Drain tuna and set aside.
Melt margarine and add enough flour to make thin gravy (this will start to thicken).
Remove from heat and add milk to make it a white sauce.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix in tuna and noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kielbasa harvest supper
directions: Parboil vegetables 10 to 15 minutes, then saute in 2 tablespoons butter.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place in a 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cut up kielbasa into serving pieces and place on top of vegetables.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with rye bread!
Enjoy!

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water just a few minutes to soften. Drain.
Mix 2 tablespoons soup with rest of ingredients.
Divide mixture among cabbage leaves.
Fold in sides; roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Bake pastry shell and set aside.
Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in a medium saucepan.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into bowl; press plastic wrap directly onto surface.
Cool to room temperature.

title: hot water cornbread(from the files of robert eugene williams)
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and seasonings to taste.
Add 1 cup hot boiling water (to the consistency of a little thinner than lumpy oatmeal).
Heat bacon drippings in cast-iron skillet.
Drop batter by spoonfuls (like pancakes) and flip when edges are brown.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Mash bananas up and add to milk, sugar and vanilla in blender and mix well.
Serve cold.

title: chocolate snowflakes
directions: Combine sugar, oil, and chocolate in a large bowl, beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla, mix well. Mix baking powder, salt, powdered sugar, and flour together then add 1/4 of dry ingredients at a time to chocolate mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and chill dough for 2 hours. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll balls in powdered sugar, place balls 2-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Cut marshmallows in small pieces if miniature ones not available.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Add to marshmallows.
Mix cut up cherries, cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together.
Add this to the pineapple mixture.
Whip cream and fold in other ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Pecans may be added if desired.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole or souffle dish and bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mussel bisque
directions: Scrub mussels.
Simmer them with spices, wine, butter and onions for 5 to 10 minutes, until shells open.
Strain.
Discard mussels.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Add cream and egg to thicken slightly.
(Do not boil.)
Serve hot.

title: white lasagna
directions: Combine flour, garlic salt and milk.
Cook over medium heat. Boil until thick.
Reserve 1/2 cup of sauce.
Mix chard into sauce.
In a separate bowl, mix 2 cheeses.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/2 cup sauce, 3 noodles and 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with 3 noodles, reserved sauce and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green beans with ham hocks
directions: In covered saucepan, cook beans in small amount of water. Before you put the beans in, cook the ham hocks until meat is almost off the bone, then put in beans.
Pour the water from the can off; rinse the beans off, then place them in pot with the meat.
Cook until tender.
Cook this about 25 minutes.
Ten minutes before you cut the beans off, add the onion, cut up in small pieces.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Cool, then serve.

title: easter rice cheese cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn oven off and let sit in oven for 1/2 hour.
Take it out and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine all-bran and boiling water and let stand for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased tin cans for 45 minutes at 350°.
Greased loaf pans may also be used.

title: earthquake cake(german chocolate upside-down cake)
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Put 1 cup of chopped nuts and 1 cup coconut in bottom of pan. Mix chocolate cake mix as directed and spread over nuts and coconut. Cream the cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar. Pour over cake, being careful not to touch sides of pan. I use a spatula to swirl mixture through cake mix a bit. Bake for about 50 minutes in oven heated to 350°. Let set for 30 minutes and turn out.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in water.
Pour over prepared vegetables.
Let stand 12 to 18 hours in cool place.
Drain thoroughly.
Add spices, hot pepper and sugar to vinegar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer until thoroughly heated.
Pack boiling hot into sterilized jars.
Leave 1/8-inch space at top.
You may use 1 red hot pepper if you want to, but not for sweet pickles.

title: deviled cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese, onion and pepper; add eggs, seasonings and mayonnaise.
Mix well and spread on bread or crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in warm water;
add cake mix, salt and enough flour
so you can handle the dough.
Knead then put in pan
to rise.
When
double in size, punch down and divide in half.
Roll out,
then	put cinnamon, brown sugar, oleo, nuts and
raisins
on dough.
Roll
up jelly roll fashion.
Cut in 1/2-inch
slices. Have ready 2 (9 x 12-inch pans).
Have oleo and
brown
sugar
in bottom of pan.
Place rolls on top.
Let rise and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
May be put in refrigerator and baked next day. Be sure and let rise.
Will take a little
longer
to bake.
A powdered sugar and water glaze can be put over top if you wish. Very good.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Pour boiling water over flowers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain flowers; boil liquid.
Bring to a simmer for 20 minutes.
When cool, add the lemon juice and rind.
Add the orange juice and rind. Add sugar and yeast.
Let stand one week, then strain and bottle, but do not put the cork in tight.
Enjoy.

title: upside down pizza
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion until no longer pink, drain.
Add sauce and simmer until heated through.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add milk and then the sifted dry ingredients. Add apples and nuts last and mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: ranch style chicken
directions: Crush Doritos and place evenly in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread chicken over Doritos.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese in bowl; pour on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° until hot (about 20 minutes), then sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Place in oven until melted (about 5 minutes).
Let cool for 10 minutes, so it won't be runny.
Can be made the night before and cooked right before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy, then add sugar and cocoa. Beat well and add milk and margarine.
Last add vanilla.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.

title: meat loaf with pecan stuffing
directions: Combine
beef
with
green
pepper,
onion, salt, sauce, white bread crumbs, milk and 1 egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Place 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of greased loaf pan.
Combine 1 egg, fat,
whole wheat
bread crumbs, celery, black pepper and meat stock
or water.
Add
to this chopped pecans; mix thoroughly. Spread
on top of meat mixture.
Arrange remaining meat mixture on top
of pecan
stuffing.
Bake
at 350° for 1 1/2 hours and cool slightly before removing from pan.
Serves 10.

title: shrimp and cheese ball
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Mix.
Add cream if necessary to blend well.
Form into a ball and chill overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers on top, then butter.
Bake another 20 minutes watching that crackers do not burn.
Serve warm or hot.

title: easy chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken, remove cooked chicken and strain broth through a colander.
Cover broth and keep in refrigerator until cold and fat congeals on top.
Pick the chicken off bones, skin and fat, etc., and leave in refrigerator overnight with broth so fat can easily be removed.
Cut up chicken meat and add to broth.
Add can of chicken noodle soup, can of mixed vegetables and ginger.
If you need a larger amount, add extra can of broth or vegetables and for creamy look, add chicken gravy or cream of chicken soup.

title: golden omelet
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour into skillet.
Cook slowly.
As egg mixture sets, lift slightly with spatula to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
Place 3 slices of Velveeta on omelet.
Fold in half. Remove from skillet.
Top with remaining Velveeta.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut in thin slices.
Peel and slice onions. Combine onions and cucumbers; add salt.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain.

title: home made chicken noodle soup
directions: Wash, cook chicken in kettle of water.
Take chicken out, cool and pick meat off bone.
Put meat in kettle and add salt and pepper.
Cover with water and add vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes, fill kettle with water leaving enough room to add noodles and soup. Add soup base (2 Tbsp.).
Check taste, add tomato soup for color, then noodles (when soup is hot).
Cover and cook till noodles are tender 15 - 20 minutes.

title: cajun sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock pot and cook until sausage is tender.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix well all 6 ingredients; pour into pie crusts.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: 4 bean casserole
directions: Save 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Drain butter beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Add all ingredients and heat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan sprayed with Pam.
In small bowl, combine ingredients; mix well. Spread sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Make into balls and dip in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: jewish cookie bars
directions: Cream margarine, cocoa and sugar and add eggs.
Mix and add flour and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.
Mix coconut and sweetened condensed milk.
When cake is cool, spread on coconut and condensed milk mixture.
Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.
Add nuts.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Put in midget paper baking cups.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to oil mixture a little at a time.
Add flavorings and fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in prepared tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes (or until done) at 325°.
Cool on rack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with sharp grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake until top is lightly browned.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add onions, salt and pepper; simmer slowly over low heat for 10 minutes or until onions are very brown and tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, consomme and water.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add the toast and serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, 1/4 cup of sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make well in center of flour mixture.
Combine milk, egg and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Toss blueberries and 2 tablespoons of sugar together.
Gently stir into batter.
Fill paper-lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for about 25 to 28 minutes.
While muffins are still warm, dip tops in melted butter and then in sugar.
Makes 1 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: glazed cranberry chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix cranberry sauce, orange juice and margarine in saucepan.
Heat until smooth.
Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Brush with at least half of the glaze.
Bake 40 minutes, re-glazing half way through cooking time.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 of the ingredients and set aside.
Milk will be sweet even though soda is used.
Saute ground meat.
Put on absorbent paper towel to drain grease.
The next 3 ingredients are prepared and placed in separate mounds and ready to use:
onion, round cheese and jalapeno peppers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Put vegetables, onion, potatoes and chicken into casserole.
Put in soup and broth and mix well.
Mix together flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over top without mixing. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until it's brown.

title: apple rice pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in rice, apple, cheese and raisins.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased baking dish.
Combine brown sugar and remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over rice mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese and bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp and drain thoroughly. Crumble bacon; set aside.
Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems and store covered in refrigerator for another use.
Set mushrooms aside while preparing filling.

title: california chicken
directions: If preferred, other chicken parts may be substituted for chicken breasts.

title: fruit freeze pops
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle the gelatine over water; let stand 1 minute.
Add hot juice and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 6 (5 ounce) paper cups.
Freeze until partially frozen.
Insert wooden ice cream sticks and freeze until firm.
Remove from the freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Peel off paper cup.
Makes 6 pops.

title: maybelle's apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar well.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla. Mix ingredients.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 325° or until it pulls away from pan.
Use 9 x 13-inch or 11 x 15-inch pan.
Especially good served warm with whipped cream.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together. Bake at 325° in an oiled and floured angel food cake pan, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan.
Poke little holes all over top and pour over the cake a mixture of the last 3 ingredients.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles (follow package instructions), then saute butter and onions in frying pan.

title: beef oscar
directions: Broil steak to desired doneness.
Steam crab and broccoli for 10 minutes.
Prepare Hollandaise per instructions.
Place 4 to 6 ounce steak on plate, top with broccoli florets, crab meat and Hollandaise.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients to boiling. Add lemon gelatin and stir until dissolved. Cool to room temperature. Rub 6-cup gelatin mold with vegetable oil. Mix cream cheese, coconut and pineapple. Stir evaporated milk into cooled gelatin mixture. Stir in cheese mixture. Pour into mold. Chill until firm. Turn out onto lettuce leaf, if desired.

title: hearty lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and eggs.
Brown beef, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
In each of 2 (2-quart) shallow baking dishes, layer 1 cup sauce mixture, 2 noodles and 1 cup cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, remaining sauce mixture and Parmesan.

title: spitun
directions: Cook spinach according to package and drain. In a medium bowl, lovingly break up the tuna. Add the spinach and mix. Add the mayonnaise and mix. Add the bread crumbs and mix. Add half of the Parmesan cheese and mix. Add the lemon juice and mix. Gently place the mixture into a 9-inch pie plate. Top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: 1-2-3 salad
directions: Combine 2 cups water and 2 boxes pudding mix; boil for 2 minutes.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Mix pudding and jello while hot.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Let stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven 350°, grease a medium (at least 1 1/2 qt.) casserole dish.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, and flour.
Stir in cheese.	Add the drained pineapple chunks and stir until ingredients are well combined.
Transfer mixture to casserole dish. In medium bowl, combine cracker crumbs, butter and reserved pineapple juice, stirring until evenly blended, spread crumb mixture on pineapple mixture.
(You may crumble a few more crackers over the top for an extra crispy version.)	Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stew beef
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage, then drain.
Add the rest of ingredients and cook.

title: cuban black bean soup
directions: Sort and soak beans overnight; drain and discard soak water. In a 4-quart pot, saute onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not browned.
Add soaked beans, 4 cups water, bouillon cube, ham (cut into 4 to 6 chunks), bay leaves, thyme, oregano, salt and red pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove 1 cup beans from stew; mash in a bowl with potato masher or fork.
Add mashed beans to stew; stir to thicken.
Remove ham and dice.
Remove bay leaves and red pepper, if used, and discard.
Add diced meat, green pepper and rum (if desired) to beans.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve beans over rice and top with sour cream, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: rhubarb pizza
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter. Beat the egg and milk together and add to make batter for crust. Press in bottom of 9-inch square pan.

title: german potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 3/16-inch thick.
Place in large utility dish and cover with plastic wrap; microwave until done.
Slice red onions in rings.
Mix slowly the salad oil and vinegar in mixer, then add beaten eggs.
Next comes the sugar, salt and pepper and finally the basil.
Place onions on top of potatoes.
Pour sauce over top.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring over medium heat. Stirring constantly, boil rapidly about 5 minutes, until mixture reaches 260° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda quickly but thoroughly.
Pour at once over popcorn. Stir gently until kernels are coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Turn out on wax paper and cool completely. Break into small clusters and store in airtight container.

title: southern style hush puppies
directions: Into a mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk and onion.
Stir with fork until moistened.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Dip with small spoon and drop into hot oil in deep pan. Fry 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve at once.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use cream cheese or whipped cream for topping.

title: hopping john
directions: Cook bacon in medium saucepan until crisp.
Add onion and celery; cook until lightly brown.
Add peas with liquid.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add water; bring to boil. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: mother's skillet candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut off ends of potatoes; slice lengthwise about 1/4 inch thick.
Mix water, sugar and butter together in an electric skillet with temperature set at 300° to 350°.
When mixture starts to get caramelly, add sweet potatoes in layers.
On each layer, sprinkle small amount of cinnamon,
small amount of vanilla (put thumb over opening of bottle and shake out) and a very small amount of lemon juice (do same as with vanilla).
Cover and cook until potatoes are fork-tender (about 20 minutes).

title: grandson's favorite manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic powder.
Drain and cool.
Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and mayonnaise; mix well.
Cook according to package directions 14 to 16 manicotti shells.
Drain; cool on wax paper.
Fill each shell with meat and cheese mixture. Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, covered with foil, for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil; bake another 10 minutes.

title: bananas foster
directions: Place butter in 2-quart shallow casserole. Microwave at High for 55 seconds or until melted. Stir in sugar and cinnamon. Microwave at High for 30 to 45 seconds or just until hot; stir well. Gently mix in bananas; microwave at High for 1 to 2 minutes. Stir gently.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter. Sprinkle 1 cup graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips over coconut. Sprinkle chocolate chips over butterscotch chips.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over chocolate chips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all, all around the pan.
Sprinkle with a little salt and bake for 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Heat last 3 items together to make sauce.
Wrap chicken pieces into crescent rolls.
Cover with sauce and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(I have also put some broccoli inside Chicken Roll-Ups.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Tear bread in pieces into large mixing bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Form lightly into loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: oven barbecued swiss steak
directions: Season meat well on both sides, then coat meat by dipping in flour.
Brown slowly on both sides in hot shortening or oil. Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients, except onion slices, and pour over meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add onion slices.
Cover and bake in skillet or Dutch oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut in colander.
Put in large bowl.
Add celery, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Dissolve sugar and vinegar; add oil.
Mix good with other ingredients.
Let stand several hours in refrigerator, covered.
Stir often.
Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs; then add melted butter and milk to them.
Combine egg mixture with dry ingredients; stir in rind and berries.
Fill well-greased muffin tins about 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sherried fruit casserole
directions: Drain all fruit.
Cut apple rings and pineapple slices in half.
Arrange fruit in layers in 2-quart casserole.
Set aside.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and cook about 1 hour on low heat.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in banana.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt into creamed mixture; mix well.
Fold in undrained pineapple and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute onion and green
pepper
in
butter or oleo until tender, but not brown.
Blend
in
flour
and
salt.
Stir
in chicken broth, cream, paprika
and
cayenne
pepper.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens
and
bubbles.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks,
return
to hot mixture.
Cook and stir over low heat about 1 minute.
Stir in chicken or turkey, sherry and mushrooms (drained).
Cook until thoroughly heated. If a deeper color is desired, add
a
dash
or two of turmeric powder. Serve in patty shells or
over
toast points or toast cups.

title: taco soup
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, corn, tomato sauce, mushrooms and taco seasoning.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with avocado, grated cheese, sour cream, chopped onions and corn chips.
This freezes well.

title: chocolate peanut butter dessert(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Mix the 2 tablespoons milk into the peanut butter.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Pour the 2 cups skim milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until blended.
Spoon whipped topping mixture and pudding alternately into 6 parfait glasses.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: heart healthy chicken fajitas
directions: In small mixing bowl, mix Italian dressing, red pepper flakes, pepper sauce, salt, pepper, soy sauce and lime juice.
Add chicken and marinate for 1 hour, unrefrigerated or 3 hours, refrigerated. In large frying pan, heat oil then add onions and peppers; stir-fry until onions are translucent.
Broil chicken until done, saving leftover marinade.
Cut chicken into 1-inch strips and add to pan with onions and peppers along with leftover marinade. Stir-fry for 1 minute, mixing well.
Then fill tortilla with stir-fry and other optional ingredients.
Very tasty low-fat recipe.
This is a real treat.
Serves 4.

title: marshmallow fluff (peanut butter fudge)
directions: Boil sugar, milk and oleo to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla.
Beat until firm.
Pour out on waxed paper.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 small package of strawberry jello.
Add a couple drops of red food coloring.
Put strawberries in shell and pour mixture over berries.

title: potato dish
directions: Cut raw potatoes (with skins on) into small pieces.
Mix with soup and oil.
Put into baking dish.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Combine pecans, raisins, cherries and pineapple.
Crush vanilla wafers and mix with fruit mixture.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Shape into rolls and wrap each in foil.
Then refrigerate.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then add shortening and milk. Roll out on floured board and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake about 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy bake fish
directions: Marinate fish in dressing 1/2 hour, then roll in crushed cracker crumbs.
Cook on High for 5 minutes per pound.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Prepare instant potatoes as you normally would, but make kind of thick.
Cook hamburger and onion until light brown.
Drain and pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread beans over hamburger. Add salt and pepper.
