Spread tomato soup over beans.
Top with mounds of mashed potatoes.
Cover with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box and let cool. When cooled, crumble cake and then add other ingredients, adding milk last.
Mix well and pack into container such as fruit cake tin with glass in center or can be rolled into logs.
Chill overnight and store in refrigerator as this one keeps for a long time.

title: caramel apple sundae
directions: Peel
and
core
apple.
Slice	into
bite size pieces. Heat apple dip and pour over apple pieces.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: tortilla trap
directions: Place tortilla on plate.
Arrange cheese on tortilla without overlapping.
Top with peppers.
Fold in half.
Cover.
Microwave on High 25 to 40 seconds, or until cheese begins to melt.
Let stand, covered, 1 minute.
Fold into quarters.
Serve with chunky picante sauce.
Makes one serving.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix everything together except pecans, then stir in pecans. Pour into one (9-inch) unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
May be a little shaky in the middle, but will firm up when cool.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream sugar with Crisco, eggs (well beaten) and vanilla, then add sifted flour and salt.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread with spoon on floured 9 x 13-inch cookie pan (with lips).
Spread filling on top.

title: cheese thins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make into little balls.
Put on baking sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scotch cakes or melting moments
directions: Roll in balls and mash with fork.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and butter in skillet.
Add garlic; cook until lightly browned.
Cool slightly. Add water slowly.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper and oregano. Blend flour with enough clam juice to make a smooth paste. Stir in. Add clams and clam
juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Makes about 3 cups.
This is very rich so a little goes a long way.

title: coke cake and topping
directions: Bring Coke, cocoa, margarine and oil to a boil.
Sift the dry ingredients and pour boiled mixture over this.
Then add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; beat together until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: meg's mock meat loaf for vegetarians(cottage cheese loaf)
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Unmolds nicely for slicing.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: Brown chicken (chicken can be skinned).
Add remaining ingredients; cook slowly, covered, until chicken is falling apart. Remove bones.
Serve over pasta with crusty French bread.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Scald milk and pour over the shortening.
Add salt, sugar and nutmeg.
Cool until lukewarm; add beaten egg and yeast, which has been softened in the warm water.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead thoroughly and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Fry in deep fat, which should be 360°.
Cook about 2 1/2 minutes each.
Makes about 3 dozen doughnuts.

title: golden rum cake
directions: Beat the eggs about 2 minutes.
Mix eggs with rest of ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Crumble chopped nuts into greased Bundt type pan.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: tasty doughnuts
directions: Add enough flour to the other ingredients to make dough easy to handle and roll. Fry in deep fat.

title: noodle dinner
directions: In skillet, cook beef until brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes and corn.
Add seasoning pack from the noodles.
Stir broken-up noodles into beef mixture.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes until noodles are tender.

title: scandinavian fruit soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except apple.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add apple cubes, simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Remove cinnamon. Serve warm or cold as a dessert. Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp k k
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper, garlic and 1/2 green onions in butter.
Add tomato paste and sugar and cook 1 hour.
Add shrimp and remaining green onions.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Beat egg into creamy mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 3 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool about 1 minute and put on foil.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese; stir well until blended.
Spoon mixture into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: cinnamon-apple saute
directions: Heat oil and butter in skillet until foamy.
Add apple rings and saute briskly over moderately-high heat.
When apples are hot, about 8 minutes, sprinkle in cinnamon.
Toss in pecans and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer.

title: sherran's barn stew
directions: Heat oil in an 8 qt. stock pot.
Cook chicken, onions, peppers and garlic until chicken is no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 - 2 hours.
Can be served over rice or with a dollop of sour cream and shredded cheddar cheese.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Place in a crock-pot. Mix the jelly and catsup, then pour over chicken.
Cook on LOW for 6 hours.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.	Add juices from pineapple and blueberries.	Cool.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.
When	jello thickens, add pineapple, blueberries and pecans;
stir
well.
Return
pan
to
refrigerator to let jello set.
Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Place cream cheese
topping mixture on firm jello.
Add pecans on topping, if you like.

title: white chip orange dream cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg and orange peel.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels.

title: hash brown cheese potatoes
directions: Combine and place in 9 x 13-inch glass flat dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice and pineapple
directions: Precook rice; drain and cool.
Add pineapple with half of the juice.
Add cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until slightly brown.
Spread a little melted butter after baking.

title: crisp cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, peppers and onion.
Combine sugar, oil and vinegar in small saucepan and heat until sugar dissolves, let cool.
Add all mixtures together and chill at least two hours in refrigerator.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Press crescent rolls into bottom of 13 x 9 inch greased pan. Mix together, cream cheese, egg yolks, 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Put Mixture over the crescent rolls.
Put crescents on top.
Mix egg whites, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Brush on top of rolls. Bake at 350° until golden.

title: mild salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and slowly bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars, leaving 1/2 to 1-inch headspace.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: you name it cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, butter, 1 egg and pecans. Mix good and pat this into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese, 4x sugar and 3 eggs.
Mix very good.
Pour this over what you have put in pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: date nut roll(candy)
directions: Cook together sugar, dates and Pet milk until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat a few strokes.
Add nuts and butter.
Knead on a tabletop.
Knead well into powdered sugar.
It will be firm, but not stiff.
Roll into cylinder mold. Let stand 24 hours before slicing.
This recipe will make 2 or 3 rolls.
Slice only enough for occasion.
Place in tin; will keep several weeks.

title: no fat fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes for fries.
Beat egg white.
Coat potatoes with egg white.
Spray large cookie sheet with Pam.
Place potatoes on sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown, turning several times. Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash white hot.

title: quick salad dressing
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the vinegar and boiling water.
Place on heat and bring just to a boil.
Cool and either use at once or keep in the refrigerator for future use.
It can be thinned with sweet or sour cream.
Very good on potato salad.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will keep one month.

title: e-z bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use whatever amount of pecans, etc., you wish.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with baking spray.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cool and easy jello pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove remaining ice cubes. Stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Garnish with remaining Cool Whip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked apple dumpling
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Add milk.
Mix to a soft dough.
Place on floured board.
Roll into a 12-inch square. Cut into 4-inch squares. Place an apple in each square.
Cream butter with brown sugar and place in the apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Bring up the floured corners of the dough to the top of the apple and press with edges together.
Brush with milk.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with cream.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine asparagus, cream of mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add peppers and heat all ingredients. Pour in a baking pan or serving dish, cover with Italian style bread crumbs.
Heat when ready to serve.
Very good.

title: grandma ruby's pie crust
directions: Crumple the first 3 ingredients and add water;
stir and let set.
Makes top and bottom.

title: pizza crackers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place crackers on ungreased baking sheet. Spread with sauce; sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: burgundy barbecue lamb
directions: Combine wine, sugar, allspice, peppercorns, cloves and cinnamon in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes over medium heat.
Remove spices and boil until reduced to 1/3 cup.
Stir in catsup, 2 teaspoons lemon juice, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Measure out and reserve 1/4 cup sauces and reserve remaining sauce in saucepan.
Combine 1 tablespoon lemon juice and cornstarch; add to sauce in saucepan Bring mixture to a boil; cook 1 minute or until thickened, stir constantly.
Stir in cherries.
Set aside.
Trim excess fat, place in 1-quart casserole. Pour 1/4 cup sauce over chops; turn to coat.
Cover and marinate 1 hour.
Grill 5 to 6 inches from coals for 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn and baste frequently.
Spoon hot cherry sauce over chops and garnish with additional cherries.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain oil and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, cream of chicken soup and water.
Pour in baking dish.
Place skinless chicken breast on top of rice mixture. Sprinkle chicken breast with garlic powder and lemon pepper and squeeze lemon juice on top.
Cover and bake until tender at 350°.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg white in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes with jackets on.
Cook potatoes, onion and salt in boiling water until done, but not too soft.
Drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle garlic salt, parsley flakes and pimentos on top.
Cube cheese and put on top. Cube bread and put on top.
Drizzle margarine over all and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1/2 quart strawberries; add sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes, until syrup is clear.
When slightly cooled, add rest of strawberries, sliced, and pour into prepared pie shell.

title: dianne's baked beans
directions: Place baked beans in casserole.
Spread bacon over top.
Mix catsup, onion, brown sugar and pickle relish; spread over bacon and beans.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients on medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and 1 heaping spoonful of marshmallow.
Stir until smooth and put in prepared 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: summer spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain, rinse with cold water.
In large bowl mix salad dressing.
Add garden vegetable mix.
Add marinated mushrooms, then add salad spice, about 1/2 jar.
Add garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Let sit for 2 hours.
Garnish with sliced tomatoes.
Enjoy.
Great for cookouts and parties.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Saute chicken in oil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add carrots and saute 5 minutes.
Add onion and saute 5 to 10 minutes.
Add wine, salt, vinegar, sugar, chile pepper and ginger and heat.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Drop tomatoes in a pan of boiling water for 15 to 20 seconds. Immediately rinse with cold water.
Remove skins.
Cut in half crosswise.
Squeeze out and discard seeds.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in confectioners sugar, beating until smooth.
Spread quickly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: In blender container, combine ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: overnight barbecue sauce
directions: The following barbecue recipe can be used with any type of meat or poultry item.

title: naked apple pie
directions: Beat egg and stir in sugars and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into first mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread on a greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.
Serves 5.

title: spinach omelet(a green vegetable dish that my husband actually likes)
directions: Whisk eggs with a little water until well mixed.
Heat 8 or 10-inch skillet; add a little bacon grease or butter and pour in eggs.
Lift edge of eggs as they are cooking and tilt pan to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
When eggs are set to your liking, arrange remaining ingredients over half of omelet.
Fold in half and cook briefly to heat filling and serve immediately.

title: acorn squash
directions: Remove seeds from squash; place cut side down in a shallow pan.
Pour water in pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn up and fill with a mixture of remaining ingredients.
Heat in center for 15 minutes.

title: swedish meringue pie
directions: Combine egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Beat with mixer until mixture forms soft peaks. Gradually add sugar and beat stiff.
Add rolled crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Hand stir gently to mix.
Heap into buttered 9-inch Pyrex pie dish. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cover with the Cool Whip. Sprinkle with grated chocolate. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and stir continually over moderate heat in saucepan until mixture becomes thickened.
Yields 1 cup.

title: "scallops" sauté
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking oil or spray. Place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Add peas and celery; saut 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables from skillet using a slotted spoon; set aside. Add scallops and next 4 ingredients to skillet.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until scallops are opaque.
Add vegetables and cook until heated.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, cheese, chicken soup, sour cream, onion and 1/2 stick butter.
Put in long baking dish.

title: clay
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in plastic bowl; then add water gradually.
When it forms ball around spoon, knead dough well, adding water if it's too crumbly.
This clay can be baked.

title: baked eggs
directions: Put bread crumbs in greased 9 x 13-inch (or 10 x 14-inch) pan. Mix all ingredients together and pour in pan over bread.
Set in refrigerator overnight before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
This recipe is great for brunch or large crowd.

title: coating for baking pans
directions: Blend the three ingredients together in food processor or Mixmaster.
Store in refrigerator in covered container until ready to use.
Coat baking pans with paper towel dipped into coating.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well; make into balls.
Squash with bottom of a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together first 3 ingredients; salt and pepper.
Mix in mayonnaise and fold in grapes.

title: 3 layer carrot cake
directions: Can be baked in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.

title: gilroy potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly oil a 9 x 13-inch shallow baking dish.
Put olive oil in a small bowl and dip each piece of potato.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with herbs.
Add at least 3 whole unpeeled garlic cloves for each whole potato. Drizzle remaining oil over all.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: island sweet-sour meat balls
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, milk and 3/4 teaspoon salt. Add meat and mix well.
Shape into 24 (1-inch) balls.
In large skillet, brown meat balls in hot shortening.
Drain off excess fat.

title: harker's island shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Boil cleaned shrimp until done. Mix other items in a large bowl.
Dice shrimp.
Add macaroni and shrimp to mayonnaise mixture; mix well.
It is better the second day when flavors have had a chance to blend, if it lasts that long.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Combine everything (except tomatoes).
Stuff tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: ham enchiladas
directions: In bowl, combine
ham,
onion
and green pepper.
Place 1/3 cup
of
mixture
and 3 tablespoons shredded cheese at one end
of each tortilla; roll up.
Arrange tortillas, seam side down, in
a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs,
cream, flour, salt, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce. Pour
over tortillas.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Bake,
uncovered, in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until
set. Sprinkle
with
remaining cheese.
Bake 3 minutes more or
until cheese is melted.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine macaroni, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, green onions and pepperoni.

title: gonzales country jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake like cornbread.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and canned milk to soft ball.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and nuts.

title: carrot-raisin-pineapple salad
directions: Mix together the carrots, celery, raisins and pineapple.
Add mayonnaise. Chill.

title: onion chops
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops in oil.
Remove from pan.
Peel and thinly slice onion.
Saute in skillet.
Blend in flour and mustard.
Add beef broth and cook for 5 minutes.

title: hazel's hot chicken salad
directions: Combine
chicken,
water
chestnuts, pimentos, almonds, mushrooms,	lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Place in a buttered 2 quart
casserole.
Top
with
cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden.
Freezes well. Serves 6.

title: cherry pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with 1/2 pastry.
Save remaining and refrigerate both while making filling.
Put pitted cherries in bowl and toss thoroughly with tapioca sugar and lemon juice and almond extract.
Let stand for 10 minutes and pour into unbaked shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and seal edges. Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°
and continue baking for 40 minutes more.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar until thick.
Combine this with margarine, flour, chocolate morsels, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: granny's banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, milk and flavorings.
Gradually add soda, salt and flour.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: apple tapioca
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put apples in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples and bake 15 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in skillet with onion and peppers in oil.
Mix beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, ginger and sugar together.
Add to steak and simmer until it thickens.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: mint iced tea
directions: Steep mint and teabags in boiling water 8 minutes.
Cool and strain.
Combine 1 cup orange juice and juice of 2 lemons, 1 cup sugar, and 6 cups cold water.
Combine.
Double for a large luncheon.

title: lemon bars deluxe cookies
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Cut butter into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Spoon flour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Press into pan evenly and firmly using fingertips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine 1/2 cup flour and baking powder and set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice; beat well.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture and pour into baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and set.
Spread top immediately with Lemon Frosting.

title: pyrenees chicken
directions: Finely chop the garlic; mix well with eggs in medium bowl. Slice chicken breast halves horizontally to have 2 thin slices shaped like the original.
Soak chicken slices in garlic-egg at least one hour or overnight.
Heat olive oil in skillet.
When oil is hot, dip each slice of chicken in crumbs to coat and add to oil.
Fry until golden, turning once.
Serve with lemon slices or Hollandaise.
Great cold for picnics, too.

title: cereal snack food
directions: Stir together and spread on cookie sheets.
Break apart when cool.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Empty biscuit mix into large bowl.
Stir in water and beat with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack before slicing.

title: zucchini and rhubarb bread
directions: Mix rhubarb, orange juice and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until rhubarb is tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain rhubarb and throw liquid away.

title: boiled cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, mix butter, milk, sugar and cocoa.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper.
If they are too thin, add more oats.
As dough cools, it will thicken.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Layer cucumbers in bottom of salad bowl.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Layer tomatoes, green pepper and onions, adding salt and pepper between each layer.
Top with olives.
Mix oil, vinegar and garlic and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight, basting occasionally with dressing.

title: almond toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Sprinkle 1 cup almonds evenly.
Place crackers on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup almonds on crackers.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and bring to boil.
Cook 3 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over crackers and spread gently.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly and sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup almonds.
Cool in refrigerator until hard.
Peel away foil and break or cut into pieces.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Melt shortening in a heavy skillet.
Add ground beef, onion, garlic and parsley.
Brown lightly.
Combine tomato paste with water, sugar, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add noodles, cover and cook until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine and let stand 1 hour.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together.
Let sit for 1 hour and serve.

title: christmas green salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes; dissolve in boiling water.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt; refrigerate until it begins to jell.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: pancho's hot dip
directions: Place all except oil in blender.
Puree for 3 seconds.
Put in saucepan and heat just to boiling.
Cool and add oil.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg and flavorings and mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and stir. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add sifted ingredients to apples with remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch size glass pan that has been greased and floured.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Spread over refried beans.
In layers, place green chillies, green onions, diced tomatoes, cheddar cheese and shredded lettuce.
Use as a dip with tortilla chips or raw vegetables.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot for about 2 to 3 hours on low, then serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Layer everything 3 times. Top with parsley and paprika. Mix the cottage cheese, mayonnaise and oil and then add 1/3 of it to each layer.

title: easy pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix can of crushed pineapple (juice and all), package of instant vanilla pudding, sour cream and sugar.
Mix all together and pour in graham cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
This is quick and easy.

title: crustless artichoke quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 8-inch pie pan with a little of the marinade.
Dice artichokes and scatter them in the pie pan with the cheese.
Combine marinade with the cream or milk to make 1/2 cup.
Beat eggs with cream mixture and pour in pan. Bake 25 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Let set 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cream of tartar; boil together until it reaches hard crack on thermometer, about 310°.
Stir in cream of tartar and pour over popcorn.
Mix well, then put on greased table top and press down to make it flat.
As soon as cooled, put in tight containers to keep it from becoming sticky.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together sherry and dried onions and let set.
Add Philly cheese, Miracle Whip, olives and beef.
Mix together and form ball.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Bring cream, milk, butter, sugar and salt to a full boil. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly over moderate heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in the chocolate chips until melted.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased pan.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then the extracts.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with the buttermilk to the mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and confectioners sugar together well. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and lemon juice until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour over hot crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix water, soy sauce, soup mix and ginger in small bowl. Heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat in large skillet. Add peppers and garlic. Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes until tender-crisp. Remove. Heat remaining oil in skillet. Add beef 1/2 at a time. Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes. Remove as browned. Return beef and peppers to skillet.
Stir in soup mixture.
Stir constantly and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute. Serves 4 over rice.

title: burgundy bread
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Brush onto loaf of sliced French bread.
Broil 6-inches from flame for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with cheeses, soups and veggies.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Melt butter on low heat and add flour.
Remove from heat; add syrup and water.
Put back on stove and boil until thick.
Cook 5 minutes; mix often.
Remove from heat.
Cool before putting into pie shell.
Put on whipped cream.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken until the meat falls off the bone.
Remove from water and let cool.
Add chicken broth to water and let it come to a boil.
Add Reames noodles and cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and chicken.
Simmer until soup is blended.
Season to taste.

title: lazy man's dish
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Put 1/2 on bottom of greased casserole.
Layer the hamburger and diced onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with remaining potatoes.
Top with soup and water. Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and milk powder, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper and soup.
Cook until bubbly, stirring often.
Add cooked macaroni, peas and turkey to sauce.
Stir gently.
Pour into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; mix well.
Spread over cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pickled peach salad
directions: Boil water with vinegar.
Pour into gelatin and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add peach juice.
Blend.
Add peaches and pecans.
Pour into a square glass dish and refrigerate until congealed.
To serve, cut into squares and put on bed of lettuce. Top with a dollop of mayonnaise.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cream cheese pecan pie
directions: In small bowl, beat together cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Beat 3 eggs slightly.
Add corn syrup, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Stir in chocolate and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, olives, onion flavor, seasoning salt and garlic salt.
Let get hot.
Boil noodles.
Put noodles layered in pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Pour meat mixture on top of layer.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top. Repeat this step 2 or 3 times.
Put into oven on 375° for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: mexican appetizer roll-ups
directions: Mix salmon, cream cheese, salsa, cumin and cilantro.
Place mixture on each tortilla; spread on surface and roll up jelly roll style.
Serve as is or chill and cut into fifths with serrated knife and serve as appetizers.
Serve with bowls of salsa (red and green) for dipping.
Fresh cilantro is best (can be made without cumin).

title: hobo dinners
directions: Cut potatoes into fourths.
Cut carrots into sticks.
Quarter onion.
Make 4 to 6 hamburger patties.
Place each patty on a square of aluminum foil.
Place potato wedges, carrots, onions on top of each hamburger patty.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fold the corners of the foil up together to form a sealed pouch.
Place each pouch on baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours until potatoes are done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage.
Crumble and drain grease.
Mix sausage with other ingredients.
Shape into bite-size balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato "yum yum"
directions: Drain and mash yams.
Add all other ingredients to the yams, mixing well after each addition. Place in baking dish and cover with topping.

title: old-fashioned potato cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in potatoes.
Stir until blended.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and garlic in 3-quart saucepan until hamburger is light brown. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes (with liquid), celery, chili powder, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Stir in beans. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until desired consistency (1 hour).
Makes 5 servings.

title: herbed baked tomatoes
directions: Thickly slice tomatoes and layer half of them in an ovenproof baking dish. Mix vinegar, mustard and garlic together. Stir in 2 teaspoons of cold water. Sprinkle the tomatoes with half of the fresh herbs and drizzle half of the dressing over the tomatoes. Lay the remaining tomato slices on top, overlapping them and drizzle the rest of the dressing. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top of tomatoes. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 25 minutes or until top is golden brown. Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining herbs. Serve immediately.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together. Add chopped tomatoes, taco mix, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing, beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: woody's spareribs
directions: Cook spareribs for 1 hour at 350°.
Combine remaining ingredients.
After cooking spareribs for 1 hour, pour off grease and put mixture on often and cook an hour longer.
Use like a basting sauce.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Marinate beef in sauce 30 minutes.
Cut tomato, onion and pepper into bite-sized pieces.
Arrange alternately on small skewers.
Cook on grill until meat reaches desired doneness.
Turn once.

title: dump-it-in cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together in a bowl.
Pour over the margarine.
Do not mix.
Add fruit; do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey baked onions(from mary mac's tea room)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel and quarter onions.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Mix in a separate bowl:
1 1/2 cups tomato juice, 1 1/2 cups water, 6 teaspoons melted butter and 6 teaspoons honey.
Pour over onions and bake at 325° for one hour or until soft.
Great side dish.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place breasts between clear plastic wrap; pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
Remove wrap; sprinkle with salt.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon parsley and 1 tablespoon green onion on each cutlet. Cut butter into 8 sticks and place 1 stick on each cutlet.
Roll chicken as for jelly roll, tucking in sides.
Press end to seal. Dust each roll with flour and dip in beaten eggs, then roll in bread crumbs. Chill thoroughly, at least 1 hour.

title: pasta tomato salad
directions: Combine tomatoes and their juice, pepper, cucumber, salt, pepper and oil in a large bowl. Toss gently. Add onion, garlic and parsley. Toss again. Cover and let stand at room temperature 2 hours for flavors to blend.

title: oven roasted chicken
directions: Skin, bone and split chicken breasts.
Pound into thin cutlets between sheets of wax paper with a mallet.
Lightly beat egg substitute or egg with water.
Mix Herb Blend with bread crumbs. Dip cutlets in egg mixture, then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: italian style chopped sirloin
directions: Shape chopped sirloin into 4 (1-inch) oblong patties.
Bake in baking pan for 15 minutes or until done at 350°.
Saute pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter until done.
Add soy sauce and cook 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
When sirloin is done, top with soy sauce mixture.
Serves 4.

title: zesty carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots after cutting into bite size.
Save liquid off cooked carrots.
Spread carrots in 9 x 9-inch baking square dish. Mix liquid, onion, horseradish and mayo.
Pour over carrots.
Top with fine bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: festive orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and whipped topping in bowl.
Sprinkle gelatin over top; mix well.
Add pineapple and oranges; mix gently.
Chill or freeze until serving time.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix in peanut butter, Cool Whip, milk and vanilla. Pour mixture into pie crust. Drizzle with chocolate syrup and freeze.

title: 1954 little bucko ginger cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, molasses, salt and shortening; add dry ingredients.
Then add liquid.
Drop on greased tins.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir oatmeal and melted margarine together.
Blend in eggs and sweetener.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix in raisins alternately with milk and vanilla.
Drop on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar; roll to coat thoroughly.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until slightly browned at edges.
Cool.

title: zuchetti met dill(zucchini with dill sauce)
directions: Sprinkle the salt over the zucchini in a mixing bowl.
Let it stand for 1/2 hour, then spread the strips on paper towels and pat them dry.
Melt the butter in a 1 1/2 quart sauce pan.
When the foam subsides, add the zucchini.
Toss it about in the butter with a spoon or spatula until well coated, then cover the pan; turn the heat to low and simmer 10 minutes, or until barely tender.
Don't overcook.
With a wire whisk, beat the flour into the sour cream. Pour the mixture over the zucchini and, stirring gently, simmer 2 or 3 minutes, until sauce is thick and smooth.
Stir in the sugar, vinegar and dill, and taste for seasoning.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Pop skins off the grapes.
Put centers in pan to boil (not too high), stirring constantly.
Remove all seeds; add skins to pulp, then stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell; dot with butter.
Cover with other pie crust; slit top crust for steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; then at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown ground beef. Combine drained noodles and beef with remaining ingredients in baking dish.
Heat until bubbly and cheese is melted in a 375° oven.

title: crunchy oriental casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and slice water chestnuts.
Saute with onion and celery in butter.
Blend together with remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with noodles. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion to taste, if desired.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix meat, noodles and sauce.
Cook in crock-pot for 1 to 2 hours on high or 3 to 4 hours on low.
During the last 15 minutes, stir in Mozzarella cheese.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets, wash and put in large bowl.
Brown the bacon and cut up over the broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over broccoli and bacon.
Stir in the cheese.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Mix all together; stuff in bird.
Leftovers go in bowl.
Cook about 2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, eggs, bananas and vanilla in mixing bowl and mix at medium speed until well blended.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add alternately with buttermilk, mixing well.
Add nuts and blend into batter.
Pour into two loaf pans, approximately 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well by hand. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 50 dozen.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Stew
four
chicken breasts, remove meat from bones and cut into large chunks.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, mix milk, soup, vegetables, chicken, Worcestershire and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Sprinkle with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend oleo and cheese.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika.
Blot olives dry.
Mold about 1 teaspoonful around olives.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in oven at 425°.
Serve warm.
May be frozen (unbaked) and use all or portions as desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes (or fresh until almost tender) and chop.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Add drained broccoli.
Put mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 400°.
Uncover; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Cook zucchini and lemon just on low heat (simmer) for 15 minutes.
Add pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Pour into jars and seal.
Serve it over biscuits or in pinwheel tea sandwiches.
This is colorful, delicious and makes nice gifts.

title: corn soup
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in 1 stick margarine. Brown the Wondra flour in frying pan.
Combine all ingredients.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender and drain. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Beat eggs, stir in mayonnaise, chopped onion and pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Add to zucchini, salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: In large skillet, melt Crisco or heat oil on medium temperature.
Cut steak into 4-inch pieces.
Flour both sides and place in heated skillet.
Lightly fry on both sides.
Drain off oil or Crisco.
Mix remaining ingredients in frying pan.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning meat frequently.
Server over large egg noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: party franks
directions: Mix prepared mustard and jelly together.
Slice franks; add to jelly and mustard mix.
Cook on low heat at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, butter and 3 tablespoons of sugar; blend well.
Assemble spring-form pan using flat bottom.
Pour crumb mixture into pan.
Press crumbs onto bottom and up sides to within 1 inch from top.

title: pork chops in creamed soup
directions: Brown pork chops and pour off fat.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup or your favorite creamed soup with water.
Cover and simmer slowly about 30 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese until softened.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Minute Maid lemonade; continue to mix until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Delicious served with fresh fruits.
Stir dip before serving.

title: lemon delight
directions: 1st Layer: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix in flour and pecans. Pat out to form a thin crust. Bake crust at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: savory meat strudel pie(6 servings)
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter or oil.
Add mushrooms and meat and stir until meat loses its pink color and is crumbly.
Turn into a large bowl and season with salt, pepper, oregano and garlic. Cool slightly.
Break in eggs, mix lightly, then mix in the cheese, parsley and bread crumbs.
Chill.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and in it place 4 to 6 layers of filo sheets, which have been brushed lightly with oil.
Spread meat mixture to cover dough and top with 4 to 6 more oiled filo sheets.
Brush top with a little oil and bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden. Let pie sit for 15 minutes, then cut in squares and serve with dollop of sour cream if desired.
Pie can be baked ahead and reheated or prepared and frozen before baking.
Preparation time: 1 hour.

title: party potatoes
directions: Before baking, mix 1 cup corn flakes with 1/4 cup butter. Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diane's pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix all ingredients and marinate.

title: vanilla chip fruit tart
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In small mixer bowl, beat butter and powdered sugar until smooth; blend in flour.
Press mixture onto bottom and up side of 12-inch round pizza pan.
Flute edge.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely. Prepare Vanilla Filling and spread on crust.
Cover and refrigerate.
Prepare Fruit Topping.
Cover and refrigerate assembled tart until just before serving.

title: puttanesca (hooker's pasta)
directions: Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan and add garlic.
Do not let burn. Add olives, capers, tomato and anchovies.
Stir and heat for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Mix flour,
salt, baking powder, baking soda and sugar. Add remaining
ingredients;
mix
well.
Bake
at
325° for 70 minutes, or
until	straw
comes
out
clean.
Butter top when done; wrap in waxed paper and put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours before using.
Keeps several weeks.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple with marshmallows and refrigerate 8 hours.
Mix flour, pineapple juice, sugar, vinegar and egg. Transfer to saucepan and cook over very low heat until thickened. Cool mixture and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Heat broth.
Add chicken, onion and rice.
Simmer until done. If too thick, add another can of chicken broth.

title: sloppy cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until brown and toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Slice cake into pieces.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, mushrooms and soup together.
Top with stuffing mix.
Pour broth over mixture.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: quick banana pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat at high speed with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Spread evenly in bottom of pie crust.
Arrange banana slices on cream cheese layer.
Spread pie filling over bananas.
Top with whipped cream and chill. Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: cajun "dirty rice"
directions: Remove tough outer skin from gizzards.
Place gizzards and livers in food processor and puree.
Heat drippings in a 6-quart Dutch oven on medium heat.
Add gizzard-liver mix and cook until browned (10 minutes).
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic and cook until transparent (5 to 7 minutes).
Add chicken broth, black and cayenne pepper; scrape bottom of pan to bring up liver/gizzard meat.
Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring often until thickened (45 minutes or so).
Fold in parsley, green onion and cooked rice.
Blend well; cook just to heat through.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple pudding pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in boiler and cook to thicken. In an oblong pan put one layer of pudding mixture and one layer vanilla wafers and so on.
Put meringue on top, using whites from 6 eggs.

title: frozen slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and 2 cups sugar together and cool.
Make tea with 2 cups water and tea bags.
Cool.
Combine sugar, water and tea when cooled.
Add lemonade, orange juice and liquor; mix well. Place in large container and freeze, stirring occasionally.

title: divinity
directions: Add 1/2 cup water to sugar; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream.
Beat until it sets.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together and put into unbaked crust. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Place broccoli, cauliflower and onion in bowl.
In blender, combine cottage cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix until smooth. Pour over veggies; toss to coat.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: pimento cheese spread or dip
directions: Have Cheddar cheese and cream cheese at room temperature.
Use mixer or food processor for cheeses.
Add remaining ingredients except pimento.
Beat or process until thoroughly mixed.
Add pimento.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Put cubed bread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cooked meat, spreading evenly over bread.
Beat eggs and add milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat in pan.
Drizzle melted butter on top; cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: milk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, & salt in saucepan. Stir in milk gradually & cook 2 minutes over medium heat until bubbly. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Stir hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks. Cook for 2 minutes longer. Add butter
& 1 tsp. vanilla, mixing well. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: busy day meat supper
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Press into a baking dish. Place potatoes and onions in layers on top of hamburger.
Mix soup and water together.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: vincie's vegetable pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add egg.
Add spices, alternating
with
applesauce.
Add flour and oats; stir well. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 muffins.

title: topsy-turvy cupcakes
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt.
Stir in the chips and set aside.

title: pickled red beets for eggs
directions: Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add eggs.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix together real well, roll into balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes. Change flavor of cake mix to make other flavors of cookies.

title: corn and onion pie
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add sour cream.
Set aside. Combine dill, muffin mix, beaten egg, Tabasco, milk and salt. Pour this mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle 3/4 cup grated cheese on top.
Add onion and sour cream mixture and top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes at 425°.
Cool slightly and cut into 9 squares.
Freezes well. Can be served with entree or as an appetizer.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Peel and core pears, then grind.
Add lemon and orange with peel.
Peel apples and chop.
Add remaining ingredients (except vinegar) and cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Add vinegar and cook about 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and set aside for 8 to 12 hours.
Knead dough in 1/2 cup of flour.
Makes into 2 loaves.
Oil pan.
Place dough in pan and turn over so oil is on top.
Cover; let sit for 8 to 12 hours.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: almond cream confection
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until butter melts and mixture begins to thicken. Remove from the heat. Add almonds or pecans and next 2 ingredients, stirring well.
Press firmly into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Cover and chill.
Spread Cream Filling over almond or pecan mixture.
Cover and chill. Cut into squares. Remove from pan and place about 1/2-inch apart on baking sheet. Set aside.
Melt chocolate.
Using scissors, snip a tiny hole in end of a sandwich bag.
Drizzle chocolate over Cream Filling. Yields 3 dozen.

title: sugar free walnut delights
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; add salt and pepper.
Top with 1/2 box of cheese crackers, crushed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cherry-o-cream pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with cream cheese.
Add vanilla and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour mixture into cooked graham cracker crust; chill for 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling and chill until served.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
As soon as cake is done and still hot, poke holes with a butter knife over entire cake.
Pour condensed milk over top and allow to soak in.
Next, pour butterscotch topping over entire top and allow to soak in.
Refrigerate overnight.
In a food processor, grind up candy bar (grinds better if cold).
Spread top of cake with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with candy bar crumbs and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: With mixer, blend potatoes, cream cheese, onion, eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat at high speed.
Pour in shallow baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.
Top with onion rings and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Serves 4.

title: swiss ham-ring-around
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
In large mixing bowl, combine parsley, onion, mustard, oleo and lemon juice. Blend well.
Add cheese, broccoli and ham.
Mix lightly.
Set aside.

title: wendy's dump bars
directions: Add ingredients and mix as listed.
Add the chocolate chips after everything else is mixed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hot punch
directions: Heat together until red hots melt.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage in large pot until tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook rice until tender.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry slowly for 5 minutes.
Chop onion and fry with the bacon, about 10 minutes.

title: tassie cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and flour, then chill.
Mix melted butter, eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Roll cream cheese mixture into balls and press into tassie (small muffin) pan.
Fill each tassie 1/2 full with brown sugar mixture.
Top with pecans.
Bake 325-350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Blend sugars, milk and syrup.
Cook until forms a soft ball. remove form heat and add vanilla, butter, and nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Pour on wax paper.

title: classic meat loaf
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the ketchup or chili sauce in a large bowl and mix well. Coat a 9 x 5-inch meat loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and press the mixture into the pan to form a loaf. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Spread the ketchup or chili sauce over the top of the loaf and bake for an additional 35 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink inside and an instant-read thermometer inserted in the center of the loaf reads 160°. Remove loaf from the oven and let sit for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.

title: fish stew
directions: Put a little oil in black Dutch oven pot, then add all other ingredients and cook over medium heat until fish is tender.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, put milk, sugar, spices and oleo and mix well.
Mix in shaker (or use blender) 3 tablespoons flour, egg and water.
Add rice and flour mix to pan and heat 3 to 5 minutes until all hot.
Pour into individual dishes or any size dish or dishes preferred.
Let cool and serve.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Beat egg and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Sift flour and salt along with the baking powder.
Combine milk and melted margarine.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Add to sugar and egg, alternately with flour.
Put in a greased 8-inch pan.
Arrange peaches on top and press slightly into dough.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle this on top and bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (buttered), put 6 slices buttered bread; on top of bread, put a slice of cheese and one of ham.
Put a dab of mustard on top of ham.
Put the remaining buttered bread, butter side up, over the mustard.
Beat the milk and eggs until foamy and pour over top.
Cover with plastic wrap, etc. and refrigerate overnight; uncover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Heat a can of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup of milk and use as a gravy for topping.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk; allow to stand 15 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 400°.
Stir egg, oil, 1/2 cup brown sugar, chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans into oat mixture.

title: baked fish
directions: * If using swordfish, cut into size for 1 serving (portion) a piece.

title: gelatin heavenly hash
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Add whipped topping, blending until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, mandarin oranges, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour in a serving bowl or individual dessert dishes.
Chill until set, about 2 hours. Garnish with additional fruit and mint leaves, if desired.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream	softened
cream
cheese,
margarine
and
sugar together.
Add pinch
of salt and vanilla.	Add eggs, one at a time and beat
well
after	each
egg is added.
Add flour and beat at least 10 minutes.
Just beat the fire out of it!
Bake in prepared Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set in pan before removing for
about
5 minutes.
This is a smooth pound cake.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in Toll House morsels and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
May be frozen.

title: crunchy sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients until smooth and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix together the brown sugar, flour, margarine and pecans and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° as you would for a pumpkin pie.
Will be done when knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: strawberry mold cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° until the cake springs back from the pan.

title: spirited watermelon slush
directions: Place watermelon cubes in blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade and process until smooth.
In large nonmetal container, combine watermelon puree, fruit punch concentrate, water and vodka.
Cover and freeze 8 hours or overnight.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and chicken seasoning.
Heat; add cream cheese and milk in with ingredients.
Place half of noodles in pan.
Layer with soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
I like to add sliced green olives with pimentos and parsley to soup mixture.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve as steak sauce or dip for corn chips.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool; then grate.
Mix together 1/2 cup butter, celery soup, onion, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Heat, then pour over potatoes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple, then add next 3 ingredients and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Form into a ball and chill.
After it is chilled, roll in remaining chopped pecans.
Makes 2 balls.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Cook the green beans.
In skillet, melt 1/3 cup margarine over medium heat.
Add sliced onion and sliced celery.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add pimentos, cut in strips, snipped fresh dill, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Toss with the green beans.
Serves 4.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add enough boiling water to make stiff dough.
Then add sweet milk to cool and mellow dough so you can form into thick or thin patties.
Fry in hot Crisco until golden brown on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Cook on medium heat until mushy.
Add pecans and spread on Ritz crackers.

title: double chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugars. Beat in vanilla, then the egg.
Add cocoa, flour, soda and salt. Beat at low speed until mixture forms a stiff dough.
Stir in chocolate chunks.
Drop by rounded tablespoons 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes.
Cook 2 minutes before transferring to wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: coq au vin
directions: Heat the oil in a large oven-safe casserole over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and saute until brown, 3 to 5 minutes. Add the salad dressing mix and onions and toss to coat evenly. Stir in the wine and broth and cook until blended. Add the chicken. Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes, turning pieces halfway through. Remove the chicken and vegetables. Increase heat to high and boil the sauce until reduced and slightly thickened. Pour over the chicken.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: sausage almondine
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Do not drain.
Add green pepper and toss.
Add Cup-a-Soup, rice and water.
Simmer until water is gone.

title: seafood cracker spread
directions: Bring tomato soup to a boil.
Add cream cheese and mix.
Gently stir in dissolved gelatin (package of gelatin and 1/3 cup cold water).
Cool mixture for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie no. 2
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Slowly add milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into a cool, prebaked pie shell.
Chill.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Mix together in a large bowl.
Add bacon bits and onion; set
aside.
In separate bowl, mix together the vinegar, sugar and salad dressing until smooth.
Pour dressing over broccoli and cauliflower mixture.
Mix well; refrigerate.

title: doodle cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Follow directions on frozen pea package for cooking.
In large salad bowl, arrange lettuce, celery, peppers, onions and peas in layers.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over peas.
Sprinkle with sugar, then with Cheddar cheese; cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with bacon just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.
Be sure to put layers as they appear in recipe.
Do not mix.
Serves 6.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of egg.
Stir together tuna, onion, cheese, salt and pepper with remaining egg. Stir baking mix and water into soft dough.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll into rectangle and spread with tuna mixture.
Fold dough over tuna and press edges together.
Make slits across top of flat loaf.
Brush tops and sides with reserved egg.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: In medium size bowl, combine lemon juice and extract.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Add 2 egg yolks and stir until well blended. Pour into pie shell.
In a large bowl, add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat with electric mixer until stiff to hold peaks. Gradually add sugar.
Keep beating until stiff, but not dry. Using a rubber spatula, fold meringue on top of pie to cover entire surface.
Make small peaks by swirling spatula.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Cool and refrigerate before serving.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Mix and serve chilled.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined milk, margarine and egg, mixing until moistened.
Stir in cheese.
For each serving, spoon approximately 1/4 cup mixture onto hot, lightly greased griddle. Flatten slightly.
Cook until lightly browned on both sides.
Serve warm with butter.
If batter becomes too thick, add small amount of milk.
Makes 20 servings.

title: chicken salad with pecans
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: mustard pickle
directions: *Or in fresh brine made by dissolving 2 cups salt and 1 gallon cold water.

title: carrot banana bread
directions: In large bowl, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Mash bananas in small bowl.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Blend in flour mixture alternately with bananas.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; turn out of pan and cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.
Good recipe.

title: skillet soup
directions: Brown beef, onions and pepper in a skillet.
Add can of beans, tomatoes and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Let simmer for a few minutes.

title: chicken and sausages
directions: Brown sausages in heavy skillet.
Remove and cut in bite size pieces.
Add olive oil to skillet and saute garlic about 2 minutes. Brown chicken in garlic oil about 5 minutes on each side. Remove and keep warm.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream 1 cup margarine and brown sugar together.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together, add to sugar mixture and beat until well blended.
Stir in oatmeal.
Spread 2/3 of oatmeal mixture in a greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
Reserve remaining oatmeal mixture for top.

title: cheese cake with graham cracker crust
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; add condensed milk.
Add ReaLemon and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Smooth into graham cracker crust; chill overnight in 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg.
Makes 1 pie.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shorties
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in slow oven until brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Store in airtight container.

title: salsa
directions: Mix and boil in large pot for 1 1/2 hours, or until desired consistency.

title: mile hi strawberry pie
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When cool, crumble and save some for the top.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Put pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and pecans in large bowl. Mix well!
Blend in Cool Whip.
Mix very well once more. Put in airtight container.

title: miss apple's nut bread
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar, salt and baking powder until light and fluffy.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour batter into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool no racks.
Can be frozen.

title: barbecue kraut
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This will make your mouth water & tingle.

title: hot tuna fish canapes
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Add mayonnaise, catsup, cayenne, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Peel cucumber and slice paper thin. Dip cucumber edges in paprika.
Cover cracker with cucumber and pile tuna mixture in center.
Place 8 canapes on 7-inch paper plate; cover with wax paper and heat in microwave for 1 minute. To freeze, cover with aluminum foil or plastic wrap.
Remove covering and heat for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Cook this over medium heat in a heavy pan and allow to cool before putting into cream puffs.
Mix as listed and cook until thick.

title: gingerbread with lemon rum sauce(mix up gingerbread cakes--either a mix or the following.)
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon, soda and salt and set aside.
In another bowl, stir together the egg white, molasses, water and oil.
Stir molasses mixture into flour mixture just until blended.
Spoon mixture into small Bundt pans or muffin cups.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until the gingerbread springs back when pressed lightly in center.

title: nachos
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup and salsa.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Serve over tortilla chips. Top with tomato, green onions, olives and peppers.
Serves 6.

title: lazy lady cobbler
directions: Pour batter into a greased glass baking dish, then spoon on fruit mix.
Then put little pats of butter evenly over the top. The berries will sink to the bottom and the cake batter will rise. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Delicious with heavy cream or ice cream on top.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Place in 425° oven and bake for 45 minutes.

title: creole spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add half onion, green pepper and celery. Cook and add a little water every now and then for 1/2 hour. Drain.
Take tomato paste and fry with only enough oil to cover bottom of pot.
Stir for about 20 minutes.
Add water every now and then.
Add rest of onion, green pepper and celery.
Fry for 20 minutes.
Add sauce, Ragu, ground chuck and mushrooms.
Cover; reduce heat to low.
Cook for 3 hours.
Pour over noodles.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients into banana mixture (bananas, sugar and egg).
Add melted shortening.
Bake in 1 large loaf pan or 2 small ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ribbon salad(nice for christmas)
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Pour into 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until partly set.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and mayo.
Add celery and garlic salt.
Blend well.
Add onion, beef and cheese.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugars; add peanut butter, then egg and flour.
Dough will be thick.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Press balls crisscross with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; beat in sugar.
Beat in egg, vanilla and cream.
Stir in flour.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill several hours.
Place on a lightly floured board. Roll to about 1/8-inch thick; use floured cutter.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake about 8 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: excellent "play dough"
directions: Place all ingredients in pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture forms a large dry ball.
Knead dough. Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter in large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.
Press mixture into a well buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: mexican meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with grated cheese.
Return to oven just long enough to melt cheese.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw frozen bread.
Spread with mustard, garlic salt and oregano.
Place Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, ham and salami in loaf and roll up.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain 1 can fruit cocktail.
Use juice and all of the other can.
Use one small container sour cream.
Mix all together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Eat.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with juice from pineapple.
Add all other ingredients.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Pour into lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana berry brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil. Mix together brownie mix, water, oil and egg in large bowl until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 12-inch pizza pan. Bake 25 minutes.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup over low heat.
Blend in cream cheese till smooth. Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add all ingredients. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: lane cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in 3 or 4 layers.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: thyme rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 475°. Put roast, rib side down, in center of a 13 x 9-inch flameproof roasting pan and rub all over with 1 tablespoon oil. Press thyme to adhere. Season beef generously with salt and pepper. Roast beef in middle of oven for 30 minutes. Remove beef from oven and with a bulb baster, skim all but 1/2 cup fat from pan. Baste beef with fat remaining in pan. Reduce oven temperature to 375°. Roast beef 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours more or until a meat thermometer inserted into the center of meat registers 115°. Transfer beef to a platter, reserving pan juices. Let beef stand 25 minutes. (Meat will continue to cook, reaching about 130° for medium-rare.)

title: quick cobbler
directions: Prepare white cake mix per instructions on box.
Grease baking dish.
Spread fruit cocktail in baking dish.
Pour cake mix over fruit; do not mix.
Bake in oven per cake mix instructions, adding 10 minutes to time for extra moisture.
Let stand.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat and potatoes
directions: Cook
the chuck, onion, parsley and oil on top of stove. Simmer until meat is done.
Add to meat mixture one small can tomato sauce plus 1 1/2 cans of water.
Cook for 20 minutes. Place sliced potatoes in casserole dish, salt and pepper to taste and pour meat mixture over.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: corn meal patties
directions: Mix well and drop by tablespoonfuls onto a slightly greased iron griddle, not too hot.
Good with vegetables or with syrup and sausage, especially if crispy edged.

title: ten-minute microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl, stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Microwace on High 4 minutes.
Stir in salted Spanish peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown. Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Blend well with wooden spoon.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy.
Quickly pour and spread on greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1 hour before breaking into small pieces.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: Wash cranberries.
Put cranberries and apples through food chopper.
Quarter whole oranges and lemons; remove seeds and membrane and put through chopper.
Add sugar and blend.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.
Keeps well.

title: zesty coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: happy holiday turkey dressing
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine with bread and seasoning.
Toss with liquid to moisten.
Stuff the turkey firmly.
Place in preheated oven at 450°.
Bake until popcorn "pops" and blows the ass off the turkey (you don't want that part anyway!).
This makes for great holiday excitement and is a kid's favorite.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: tuna fish patties
directions: Crush saltine crackers.
Add to mixture.
After completely mixed, make round balls.
Flatten out.
Coat with cornmeal.
Put enough grease to cover bottom of skillet.
Put patties in.
When grease is hot, brown.
Turn over.
Brown both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 8 patties.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Note:
May use egg substitute and whole or skim milk.
May use low-fat cheese.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into molds or pan.
Chill until firm.

title: calvin's chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in 3 cups water until tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
While chicken cooks, heat oil in frying pan. Saute onion, green pepper, oregano and basil until onion and green pepper are soft.
Drain chicken.
Remove bones (if not using boneless) and slice each breast into 6 strips.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Make layers in a casserole dish of vegetables and cheese. Pour soup on top and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Butter a glass baking dish.

In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, salt, syrup and milk. Cook, stirring constantly. Check for consistency using small amount of cold water. In cup, drop 1 to 2 drops of chocolate until it forms soft ball stage. Then add vanilla and butter.
Stir well. Then let mixture cool until you can put your hand on bottom of pan. Then beat mixture until it turns a dull color, then pour fudge into greased dish. Let cool.
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Drain sauerkraut and press out excess liquid.
Place sauerkraut over chicken and top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted into chicken with ease.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Clean and wash gizzards.
Boil in garlic seasoned water until cooked.
Save your broth.
Make a light brown roux with shortening and flour.
Chop gizzards.
Add gizzards, roux, onions, green onions and stock from your baked turkey together in the gizzard pot.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except hamburger) for 10 minutes.
Add hamburger and simmer 1/2 hour. Can cut recipe in half.

title: cheese roll
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature and cream well.
Add grated cheese, garlic powder, salt and pecans.
Make into 2 rolls and roll in chili powder.
Chill well and serve with crackers.

title: soft molasses cookies
