directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy. Blend in molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in water.
Add flour and baking soda mixture alternately to margarine mixture; blend well after each addition.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased and floured baking sheets.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes or until done.
Remove from baking sheets and cool on wire racks.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put about 1 tablespoon of cooking oil in a large pot and heat it up.
Mince garlic or put it through a garlic press and cook in the oil until clear.
(Actually, sometimes I mess up and slightly char the garlic and this is kind of an interesting taste also.) Add onions and continue cooking until onions are mostly clear.
Add ground chuck and just barely brown it.
(If the amount of grease in the pot becomes excessive, drain it off and get leaner beef next time.)
Add remaining ingredients and stir until bubbling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for at least 30 minutes, but ideally an hour or more.
This recipe makes enough to eat a lot and freeze some in suitable containers for a later time.

title: judy's party dip
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together. Cut top off bread and hollow out the middle. Fill bread bowl with mixture and replace top. Wrap bread in foil. Bake 30 minutes in a 325° oven or until cheese is melted. This recipes makes enough filling for two round loafs of bread.

title: orange-cranberry cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Combine pineapple with eggs, cranberry sauce, oil and orange peel.
Stir into dry mixture. Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on rack 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: old fashioned stuffing
directions: Saute onions and celery in melted butter until lightly browned.
Add bread cubes and remaining ingredients. Toss lightly until well blended.
Use 1 cup of stuffing per pound of ready-to-cook turkey weight.
An 8 to 12 pound turkey should be roasted approximately 4 to 4 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
This filling is also good baked in a baking dish and used as a side dish.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over the chicken and add a little water. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain well.
Add onion, garlic salt, celery salt, salt and pepper and spaghetti sauce.
Cook for 15 minutes, then add the cottage cheese and eggs.
Cook the noodles. Place a layer of noodles on the bottom of a covered baking dish. Pour some sauce over the layer of noodles, top with the Mozzarella cheese, then the Cheddar cheese.
Repeat the procedure until out of sauce with the cheese ending up on top.
Bake at 400° for 60 minutes.

title: risdon reuben dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place first 3 ingredients in blender. Process until finely chopped.
Combine mixture with remaining ingredients.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 10 to 15 hors d'oeuvres.
Use rye cocktail bread or rye bagel chips and crackers.
This is so good during the winter months you can double this recipe for more people.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: mexican peas
directions: Wash peas.
Soak in water 2-inches above peas overnight. Brown sausage to crumble.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Then drain.
Drain peas and stir in sausage and other ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add water if needed.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine corn bread, bread, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning in a very large bowl. Brown in pan with 1/4 cup oil the celery, onion, peppers and carrots. Cook until tender, about 7 minutes. Add to corn bread mixture. Mix well. Pour into 9 x 12 greased pan. Pour eggs mixed in broth over top of corn bread mixture. Dot with butter and mix into mixture. Add more broth, if you like. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk into large mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix and mix on low speed until thickened.
Add the cream and mix on low until mixed well, about 2 minutes.
Fold the whipping topping into this mixture until it is well blended.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers on bottom of a large deep dish and a layer of sliced bananas.
Cover with half of pudding mixture.
Repeat with another layer.
Sprinkle some vanilla wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Best made a couple of days in advance.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions and chill until set. Put milk, bowl and beaters in freezer for about 1 hour (milk should be icy).
Add 1/2 sugar substitute to strawberries. (If frozen strawberries are used, they should be partially thawed.)
Beat milk with vanilla and remaining sugar substitute at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Quickly whip gelatin and strawberries together. Fold gelatin into whipped milk and mix gently until no white streaks remain.
Serves 4.
Prep time is 2 hours, 60 calories per serving.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake approximately 30 to 35 minutes; cool.

title: sue b's chess pie divine
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar.
Chop oleo into mixture.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Place over water in top of double boiler and bring to lukewarm to melt oleo.
Stir constantly.
When oleo is melted, pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 minutes at 250°, then increase temperature to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato.
Add sugar to make a tacky dough.
Roll dough on sugared surface (like a pie crust).
Spread peanut butter on top; roll up like jelly roll.
Slice and chill.

title: lettuce-pea salad(7-layer salad)
directions: Shred lettuce and spread on bottom of bowl.
Sprinkle green peas over lettuce.
Sprinkle chopped celery over lettuce. Sprinkle chopped green pepper, then chopped onion.

title: barbecued chicken sandwiches
directions: In a 3-quart slow cooker, combine all ingredients except buns; mix well. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serve on buns. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: shiitake snow peas
directions: Saut washed mushrooms in butter on low.
Stir in snow peas and soy sauce.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Toss and serve.

title: devil's food drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla; stir in chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to chocolate alternately with sour cream. Mix well.
Stir in nuts. Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: butterscotch brownies(for 96 servings, prepare on sheet pan.)
directions: Melt butter.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix butter and sugar until smooth.
Gradually add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla. Mix dry ingredients.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind together tomatoes, onions and green and red peppers. Drain off juice.
In large pot stir all ingredients together with large spoon.
Simmer over low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Pack hot mixture into jars; seal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° or 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pot roast
directions: In a Dutch oven or large heavy pan, heat oil until hot.
Add meat and brown on all sides, about 5 minutes.
Add onions; saute until tender.
Add water, Worcestershire sauce and rosemary.
Add carrots.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender in a covered pan (2 1/2 to 3 hours).

title: alma's fruit cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients except fruit and pour in pan.
Put in fruit. Pour 1 cup sugar over fruit.
Pour 1 cup hot water over sugar. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, salt and soda in bowl; set aside.
In another big bowl, cream rest of ingredients and milk (add more milk if needed).
Then mix flour mixture in with creamed ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt, sugar and Sweet 'N Low.
Beat until blended.
Top pie and brown lightly in 300° oven.

title: life recipe
directions: Mix these thoroughly and add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with gifts of love.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of Christian living.
After all, pour this into our daily lives.
Bake well with human kindness and serve with a smile.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken with celery tops and carrots in salted water for about 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in broth.
Remove and drain. Cook vegetables until just tender.
Drain and place in greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Place pieces of chicken on top of vegetables. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and a touch of water in a bowl; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs; put over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered, in a 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend butter or margarine with the stuffing.
Line baking dish (approximately 10 x 10-inch) with 1/2 of the crumbs.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish and top with the rest of the crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumber slices in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, except dill weed.
Pour over cucumbers and toss lightly.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Chill thoroughly.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well. Spray with cooking spray 8-inch square pan or casserole dish. Mix 6 rounded balls of meat loaf. Press each ball slightly in pan. Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Check meat loaf 15 minutes. Before take out time, put catsup on top. Cook the other 15 minutes. Remove from oven. "Freeze leftovers."

title: roasted pork loin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make small slits on all sides of pork. Insert garlic.
Rub meat with olive oil. Rub on salt, pepper and rosemary. Place meat on a rack in roasting pan. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours (thermometer reads 160°). Let stand 15 minutes before carving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together in order.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until broom straw comes out clean.

title: dirt cups
directions: Decorations:
gummy worms and frogs, chopped peanuts and granola.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Make both boxes of stuffing according to the directions. Lightly press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with raw chicken breasts that have been cut into bite size pieces.
Top chicken with the 2 cans of soup.
Top soup with shredded cheese; top the cheese with the onions.
Do not stir.
Cover tightly with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut squash in slices, skin and clean, then cut into 1/2-inch strips, place squash in an ungreased baking dish 11 x 7 x 1-inch or 13 x 9-inch if you double recipe.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Tear chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Add next three ingredients.
Add broth if needed.
Stir well.
Divide mixture into deep dish pie shells.
Cover with shallow dish pie shells. Cut vents into top pie shell to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: amma's cheese wrapped grapes
directions: Beat together cheeses, butter, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
With damp hands, form mixture around individual grapes. Roll each ball in paprika and then chopped nuts.
Chill.
Makes 50 appetizers.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil.
Add water, broccoli and soup. Bring to a full boil, separating broccoli pieces.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tex-mex devils
directions: Boil eggs, then cut in half.
Remove and mash yolks.
Blend in picante sauce, bacon and mayonnaise.
Refill whites.
Garnish as desired.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Over medium heat cook celery, onion and pepper in bacon fat until onion is soft.
Add garlic, tomatoes, cayenne pepper, chili powder and thyme.
Lower heat and simmer.
Add shrimp, parsley and salt, cook until shrimp is hot.
Eat over rice.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Heat water in a nonstick frypan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir frequently.
Add bouillon, water, pepper and garlic powder.

title: salmon fettuccine and cabbage
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain.
Heat vinegar and oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add cabbage; cook for 3 minutes, or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in fennel seed.
Add fettuccine; toss lightly to coat.
Add salmon; mix lightly.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add other ingredients. Roll into tiny balls or drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Boil chicken livers until done.
Mash while hot.
Add mashed hard-boiled eggs, sauteed onions, salt, pepper, chicken fat and mayonnaise until it reaches spreadable consistency.
Serve with crackers.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind sweet peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Place in a large kettle.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal immediately.
Makes 9 to 10 pints.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, then hot water. Add flour mixed with soda.
Add nuts, oatmeal and vanilla, then butterscotch chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 365° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar,
butter
and
Crisco.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating
after
each.
Mix flour and baking powder; sift twice. Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Mix in flavor and pineapple.	Bake
in
a
tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened; beat vigorously 1 minute.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen; remove from pan.
(If loaf sticks to pan, press gently on side of loaf with knife or metal spatula).
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and make well in center.
Add margarine and combine pumpkin, egg and water.
Mix to moisten. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fettucini primavera
directions: Boil fettucini as directed on package.
Drain and set aside. In Dutch oven, saute garlic in oil and margarine.
Add whole prawns and saute for 1 minute.
Remove from pan and set aside in small bowl.

title: holiday apple cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, add apples. Mix well, add eggs, corn oil and vanilla.
Beat well, add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with Glazed Icing while cake is still hot.

title: rice curry salad
directions: Mix rice, onion, oil, vinegar, salt and curry powder.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours, then add peas, celery and mayonnaise.

title: sweet pickles(9 day method)
directions: Mix salt and water to make a brine thick enough to float an egg.
Soak cucumbers in water 3 days.
Be sure all cucumbers are covered.
Remove from salt water and soak overnight in clear water.
Take from clear water and put into alum water (made by mixing 2 boxes alum with 2 gallons of water).
Leave 2 days. Remove cucumbers and slice.
Pour vinegar over and add 2 pounds of sugar and pickling spice in cloth bag.
Heat but do not boil; let set overnite.
Next day, add 1 1/2 pounds of sugar; heat again. On the 3rd day, add 1 1/2 pounds sugar.
Heat and remove spice bag.
Pack pickles into jars and cover with hot vinegar liquid. Seal jars.
Makes about 8 quarts.

title: "chocolate delight"
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° until firm (20 to 30 minutes).
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 of Cool Whip and sugar. Make layer of mixture on top of cooled crust.
Make pudding as per directions on package.
Layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: e-z do pecan log
directions: Soften butterscotch chips.
Stir in milk, pecans and vanilla. Chill until mixture can be handled.
Roll into a 12-inch log. Wrap in wax paper to ease handling.
Unroll.
Mark surface with tines of fork lengthwise.
Brush surface with egg white.
Press pecan halves on sides to cover.
Wrap in foil or plastic.
Chill. Cut into desired slices to serve.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 9 x 13 baking pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter. Top with sweetened condensed milk. Bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown. In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with peanut butter. Spread evenly over condensed milk layer. Cool 30 minutes. Chill thoroughly. Cut into bars. Garnish as desired. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: sugar biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients up together, except lard or oil.
Then when all is mixed thoroughly, mix in lard or oil.
Add raisins if desired.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° on middle shelf in oven.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Do not overbake.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of an 11 x 17-inch baking pan or cookie sheet with the crescent roll dough, pulling and stretching to fit. Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: quick manicotti
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
Drain; rinse in cold water.
Set aside.
Saute ground beef and garlic.
Drain. Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, salt and mayonnaise to skillet.
Stir.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Place stuffed shells in baking dish.
Combine spaghetti sauce, oregano and Italian seasoning.
Pour over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips until just moistened.
Add chips and stir in.
Put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan.

title: carrot bread
directions: In mixer bowl, cream sugar, oil and eggs. Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Add to creamed mixture. Mix well. Pour in greased floured loaf pan. Bake in 325 degrees oven about 1 hour and 20 min.

title: chinchin nigerian cookies
directions: Rub the butter into the flour.
Add the sugar and nutmeg; mix well.
Mix in the beaten egg, forming a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out on a floured board about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut crisscross fashion, forming small diamond shapes.
Heat oil to 350° to 375°.
Fry the dough until it browns evenly.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sausage-cabbage supper
directions: Brown meat.
Crumble sausage into a 1 3/4-quart casserole dish; add onion.
Cook, covered, on 100% power for 5 to 6 minutes or until no pink remains, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook on high for 7 to 9 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir before serving.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts in small pieces.
Mix well with cheese and mayonnaise.
Place in a small ovenproof crock or dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: graham streusel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan.
Mix crumbs, nuts, sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Save.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat and onions; drain fat.
Stir in taco mix and Ranch dressing mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with Mexican chips.

title: orange freeze pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling orange juice.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, blending until dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened; stir in mandarin oranges.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into baked pie shell and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix and cook over low heat the first 6 ingredients until it forms a paste.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts and mixture is smooth.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and blend well.
Add corn syrup, stirring constantly.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring often to prevent scorching.
Cook to 248°.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add vanilla. Pour into 9-inch square pan and let cool.
Cut into bite size pieces and wrap each individually in wax paper.

title: egg custard
directions: Scald milk.
Combine eggs, Sucaryl, salt and vanilla in large mixing bowl and blend well.
Slowly add scalded milk.
Pour into prepared 9-inch crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until done (inserted knife comes out clean).
To prepare crust, bake just until set, not completely cooked to prevent rising in custard. Serves 6.

title: bishop's bread(coffee cake)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Save 3/4 C. for topping crumbs.
To remaining batter add the other ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and scatter crumbs over the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 400 degree oven.

title: eagle brand pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk, ReaLemon and food coloring.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes; chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: favorite chocolate cake
directions: Place flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl; set aside.
Bring oleo, oil, water and cocoa to a boil; add to flour mixture and beat well.
Add beaten eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Fudge Icing.

title: lemon ice
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling in pan; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Freeze uncovered 3 to 4 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
(Mixture should be broken into tiny crystals but should not be solid.)
Serve in chilled dessert dishes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon; add to cream mixture and mix thoroughly.
Fold in rolled oats and pecans. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet; flatten if desired. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool about 2 minutes before removing from baking sheet.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Mix onion, water, salt, pepper and bay leaf in 5-quart saucepan.
Add chicken pieces, cover for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken from liquid.
Melt butter and stir in flour, parsley flakes and paprika.
Blend in reserved liquid and milk until smooth.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook and chop frozen broccoli.
Place broccoli and rice in a 2-quart casserole dish. Stir in half of the Cheez Whiz.
Melt butter in a skillet. Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender, but not browned.
Stir in soup and milk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over broccoli and rice mixture.
Mix well. Top casserole with the remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This may be made in the morning and baked when ready to serve for supper. Very good.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Use gingersnaps to dip.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Gradually add flour, salt and vanilla. Add baking powder. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in a large glass baking dish. Add salt and pepper to taste. Stir in soups, sour cream, cheese and milk.
Put butter in a separate bowl. Add corn flakes and stir.
Top hash brown mixture with corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and egg.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place balls in a pie dish.
Cover.
Microwave on Roast-medium (60%) for 8 minutes.
Drain.
Rearrange meatballs so that center ones are brought to the outside and outside balls are moved to the center.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Pour mixture over the meatballs.
Re-cover.
Microwave on Roast-medium (60%) for 6 to 8 minutes, or until meatballs are done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend and bring to a boil, stirring first 4 ingredients constantly, 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme (walnuts, if desired).
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour in a buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut and store.

title: old fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour, shortening, salt and butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Gradually stir in cold water, a little at a time, to form a dough.
Divide pastry in half.
Form each to a flat round.
Wrap in wax paper or plastic wrap and chill.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Crush strawberries into small pieces.
Add sugar; mix well. In separate bowl beat together both whipping cream and sugar.
Mix everything and pour into pie pan.
Freeze.
Peel away pan.
Serve frozen.

title: date-nut pinwheel caramel refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Form into a roll 2 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.

title: homemade vanilla pudding
directions: 1. Mix milk, eggs, cornstarch and sugar together in a 2 qt microwave safe bowl; until smooth.

title: easier cake
directions: Pour fruit cocktail in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the top.
Drizzle all with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: cran-apple jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until melted.
Add applesauce.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate-covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and oleo thoroughly.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Roll into small balls.
Add a toothpick to each ball.
Chill.
Mix chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Melt together.
Dip balls in chocolate mix and place on wax paper. Store in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot; sprinkle with garlic salt. Cover and seal with foil so no steam escapes.
Cook all day on low.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers, in a large bowl. Put in a large casserole dish or pan. Crumble Ritz crackers over top and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until crackers are brown.

title: easy chicken
directions: Saute onions and celery in mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Add cooked deboned chicken.
Simmer a few minutes.
Make into patties and brown.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pie filling and eggs. Mix by hand. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Test with toothpick.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add taco seasoning.
Layer beef, beans, rice, cheese and Doritos.
Bake at 350° until melted.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift
the
flour
and 3/4 cup sugar 3 times; set aside. Beat egg whites; add cream of tartar, salt, vanilla and almond extract until foamy.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, a spoonful at a time, to
egg mixture.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in flour and 3/4 cup sugar. Bake at 375° in a tube pan for 35 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Add all ingredients except paprika.
Beat until fluffy.
Re-fill egg whites.
Garnish with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Combine beans and taco seasoning into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Spread sour cream over beans and top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet dressing for cole slaw
directions: Mix together and pour over cabbage.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and chill.
Cream together sour cream, cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spread on well chilled jello.
Top with chopped walnuts.

title: hot diggities
directions: Mix all ingredients, except franks, in a chafing dish.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add franks and heat 5 to 8 minutes.

title: streusel topped banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 15 muffin cups. Mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup nuts and cinnamon.
Reserve.
Beat bananas, oil, milk, vanilla and egg in bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except reserved mixture) all at once, just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from muffin cups.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix together the flour, honey, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Combine egg, pumpkin, oil and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Yields 12.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Wash and sort peas. In a medium saucepan, combine peas and 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes. Drain peas, reserving liquid.
Set peas and liquid aside.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve warm with whipped cream.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well together and serve.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix sugars, flour, milk, cinnamon and vanilla together.
Pour mixture in middle of melted butter.
Pour can of fruit in middle of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Roll this, then cut into squares.
Drop it into boiling broth of pork, beef, or chicken.
Add sliced potatoes.
Cook until done.

title: white chocolate snack mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in very large bowl.
Melt white chocolate in top of double boiler.
Pour over dry mix and stir to coat well.
Spread out to dry on waxed paper (about 30 minutes). Store in airtight container; keeps well.

title: the deluxe dessert sandwich
directions: Bake cookies according to package directions.
Let cool. Soften ice cream slightly.
Cover half cookies with ice cream. Put chocolate syrup on the ice cream.
Sprinkle sprinkles on top. Place plain cookie on top.
Wrap in foil; place in freezer until firm.

title: falafel(chickpea patties)
directions: Mix the chickpeas and onion.
Add the parsley, lightly beaten egg and spices.
Whirl in a blender.
Add breadcrumbs until the mixture will form a small ball without sticking to your hands. Form the chickpea mixture into small balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Flatten the patties slightly before frying them in deep hot fat until golden brown on each side.
Drain.
Serve individually with toothpicks as an hors d'oeuvre or as a sandwich filling with chopped tomato, cucumber, radish, lettuce and onion inside pita.
Makes about 24.

title: "johnny marzetti"
directions: Brown hamburger in large pot.
Drain fat.
Add tomato puree and tomato paste plus one can water.
Add basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove
from
skillet.
Add chopped onion and pepper; fry in bacon
fat.	Add
in dish, catsup, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar,
beans, onion and pepper.
Crumble bacon on top.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Mix apples and cranberry sauce in a large baking dish, approximately 9 x 12-inches.
In a pan, melt oleo and add brown sugar, flour and oats.
Mix well (do not cook).
Spoon mixture over the apples and cranberries.
Bake one hour in 350° oven.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add cream and beaten eggs to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll quite thin and cookies are more crisp.
If cloth covered board and rolling pin are used, not so much flour will be required to roll.

title: italian sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/2 inch thick and place on greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with Italian seasonings, salt and pepper.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours until excess tomato juice has evaporated. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and broil until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chicken tacquitos(makes 40 appetizers)
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add green onions and green pepper; continue cooking for five minutes or until vegetables are tender and chicken is cooked through.
Remove mixture from skillet; drain.

title: melon bubbles
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and enough ice cubes to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin. Stir until slightly thickened.
Remove dry unmelted ice.
Measure 1 1/3 cups gelatin.
Add melon.
Pour into 7 individual dishes or medium serving bowl.
Beat remaining gelatin at high speed with electric mixer until thickened and double in volume.
Spoon over gelatin mixture in dishes.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: karo fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients until well mixed.
In medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup. Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, covered.

title: dakota bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water; stir to dissolve.
In a large bowl, mix sunflower oil, egg, cottage cheese, honey and salt.
Add dissolved yeast and 2 cups bread flour, beating until flour is moistened.
Gradually stir in whole wheat flour, wheat germ, rye flour and oats, plus enough bread flour to make a soft dough.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix well and chill. Serve with your favorite raw vegetables.

title: chicken pie
directions: Simmer chicken, salt and celery in water until tender.
Take chicken off bones, cut and arrange in a casserole.
Put fat in a separate container; add flour.
Cook and stir until smooth; add broth and milk.
Cook until thick; season and pour over chicken and eggs.
Top with pie crust and brown in a moderate oven.

title: chocolate-coconut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, sugar, milk, vanilla and egg.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Sift and stir into shortening mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and coconut or apple.
Drop from spoon onto greased baking sheet. The secret of success is to bake cookies only until outside edges begin to turn brown, 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to finish baking on sheet a couple minutes before moving cookies to rack to cool.

title: corn souffle
directions: Puree corn in blender with 1/4 cup half and half.
Add remaining half and half, cornstarch, salt and sugar; blend well. Add beaten eggs and butter; blend and pour into a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart souffle dish or straight-sided casserole.
Place dish in pan of hot water to a depth of 1-inch; bake at 400° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Serves 6.

title: german scones
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar.
In a large mixing bowl, pour boiling water over Crisco, remaining sugar and salt.
Stir to melt Crisco.
Add eggs, yeast mixture and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Let rise 1 hour at room temperature; stir down.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Roll out 1/4 of the dough into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Fry a few at a time in hot, deep Crisco at 350° for 1 minute on each side.
Drain.
Serve warm with jam.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Unused dough may be stored in the refrigerator.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rosemary pork chops
directions: Prepare grill for medium heat.
In a small bowl, combine garlic, rosemary and pepper.
Press mixture onto chops.
Grill chops 15 to 20 minutes per side or until meat near bone is no longer pink when slashed with a knife.
Serves 4.

title: cameo chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Add white chocolate, stirring until chocolate melts.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
Combine 1/2 cup flour and pecans, stirring to coat; set aside.
Combine remaining 3 cups flour, sugar and soda in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually stir in white chocolate mixture.
Fold in pecan mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until center tests done. Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.
Frost with icing.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper.
Mix all.
Put in greased casserole dish; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer all the ingredients on serving dish, starting with the refried beans and ending with the cheese.
